{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hx8s7aitb3QT6sN4LQiG7X","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide a comprehensive analysis report.\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Codebase Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase to understand all the components needed for adding an \"issue ID\" field to runs and fixing table alignment in list output. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Domain Types for Run** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (194 lines)\n\nThe `Run` struct already has a `TaskID` field (line 56):\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n\tID             string\n\tWorkflowName   string\n\tState          RunState\n\tActiveSteps    []string\n\tStepExecutions []*StepExecution\n\tStartedAt      time.Time\n\tCompletedAt    time.Time\n\tProjectDir     string\n\tErrorMessage   string\n\tContainerID    string\n\tBaseSHA        string\n\tContainerKept  bool\n\tTitle          string\n\tIsHost         bool\n\tParentRunID    string\n\tTaskID         string  // ← Already defined (line 56)\n}\n```\n\nAlso defined: `RunListFilter` struct (lines 18-25) with `TaskID` field already present.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **CLI Command Implementation - `cloche run`**\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 163-221)\n\nCurrent implementation:\n- Flag parsing supports: `--workflow`, `--prompt/-p`, `--title`, `--keep-container`\n- **NO** `--issue`/`--task-id` flag support yet\n- Calls `client.RunWorkflow(ctx, &pb.RunWorkflowRequest{...})`\n\n---\n\n### 3. **CLI Command Implementation - `cloche list`**\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 262-350)\n\nCurrent implementation:\n- **Already supports** `--issue/-i` flag (lines 291-295)\n- Flag passes `issueFilter` to `req.TaskId` in the gRPC request\n- **Table formatting issue:** Lines 325-348 build output with hardcoded spacing:\n  - Line 330: `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s  %-20s  %-10s  %-9s\", run.RunId, run.WorkflowName, run.State, runType)` \n  - Uses `%-20s` (20 chars), `%-10s` (10 chars), `%-9s` (9 chars) for workflow, state, and type\n  - Then appends optional fields with `\"  \" + field` (2 spaces), causing misalignment when fields have varying lengths\n\n---\n\n### 4. **gRPC Protobuf Definitions**\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (168 lines)\n\n**RunWorkflowRequest** (lines 25-32):\n```protobuf\nmessage RunWorkflowRequest {\n  string workflow_name = 1;\n  string project_dir = 2;\n  string image = 3;\n  string prompt = 4;\n  bool keep_container = 5;\n  string title = 6;\n  // ← NO issue_id field\n}\n```\n\n**ListRunsRequest** (lines 99-105):\n```protobuf\nmessage ListRunsRequest {\n  bool all = 1;\n  string project_dir = 2;\n  string state = 3;\n  int32 limit = 4;\n  string task_id = 5;  // ← Already defined\n}\n```\n\n**RunSummary** (lines 111-121):\n```protobuf\nmessage RunSummary {\n  string run_id = 1;\n  string workflow_name = 2;\n  string state = 3;\n  string started_at = 4;\n  string error_message = 5;\n  string container_id = 6;\n  string title = 7;\n  bool is_host = 8;\n  string project_dir = 9;\n  // ← NO task_id field\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **SQLite Store Implementation**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (499 lines)\n\n**Database Schema** (lines 46-89):\n- The `runs` table already has `task_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''` column (line 85)\n- Added in migration as part of evolution schema additions\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `CreateRun()` (lines 134-142): Inserts all 15 columns including `task_id`\n- `UpdateRun()` (lines 175-183): Updates `task_id` along with other fields\n- `scanRun()` (lines 148-162): Scans `task_id` from rows (line 152)\n- `runSelectCols` constant (line 145): `COALESCE(task_id,'')` is included\n- `ListRunsFiltered()` (lines 244-277): Supports filtering by `TaskID` (lines 256-259)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Ports/Interfaces for RunStore**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (60 lines)\n\n**RunStore interface** (lines 10-20):\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n\tCreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n\tGetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n\tUpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n\tDeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n\tListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n\tListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n\tListRunsFiltered(ctx context.Context, filter domain.RunListFilter) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n\tListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n\tListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n```\n\nAll methods already support TaskID through the `RunListFilter` parameter.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **gRPC Server Implementation - RunWorkflow**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 90-145)\n\nCurrent flow:\n1. Checks if workflow is host or container\n2. Generates unique `runID` \n3. Creates run: `domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)`\n4. Sets `run.ProjectDir` and `run.Title` from request\n5. **Does NOT set TaskID** - request has no `issue_id` field\n\n---\n\n### 8. **gRPC Server Implementation - ListRuns**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 425-458)\n\nCurrent implementation:\n- Builds `RunListFilter` from request (lines 426-431)\n- Calls `s.store.ListRunsFiltered(ctx, filter)` \n- Builds response by iterating runs and converting to `pb.RunSummary` (lines 444-456)\n- **Does NOT include `task_id`** in response (RunSummary proto has no task_id field)\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Help Documentation**\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` (lines 167-194)\n\nCurrent `cloche list` help text:\n```\nFlags:\n  --issue, -i ID     Filter by issue/task ID.\n\nOutput columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\ntitle, container ID, and error message (if any).\n```\n\nThe `--issue` flag is already documented.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Related Components**\n\n**Help for `cloche run`** (lines 58-83 in help.go):\n- Shows flags: `--workflow`, `--prompt`, `--title`, `--keep-container`\n- No `--issue` flag documented yet\n\n**Host Workflow Runner** (`/workspace/internal/host/`):\n- The `host.Runner` struct already has `TaskID` field (used in phase loop setup)\n- Lines in grpc/server.go (e.g., 962, 1006) show TaskID being passed\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Required Changes\n\n### For adding \"issue ID\" field to runs:\n\n1. **Proto file** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`):\n   - Add `string issue_id = 7;` to `RunWorkflowRequest`\n   - Add `string task_id = 10;` to `RunSummary`\n\n2. **CLI `cloche run`** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`):\n   - Add `--issue`/`-i` flag parsing to `cmdRun()` \n   - Pass to `client.RunWorkflow()` request\n\n3. **gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`):\n   - In `RunWorkflow()`: Set `run.TaskID = req.IssueId` before storing\n   - In `ListRuns()`: Include `TaskId: run.TaskID` when building `RunSummary`\n\n4. **Help text** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go`):\n   - Add `--issue` flag documentation to `cloche run` help\n\n### For fixing table alignment in `cloche list`:\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 325-348)\n\nThe current approach concatenates fields with hardcoded spacing. Should use proper column formatting with consistent delimiters to ensure alignment regardless of field widths.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations Summary\n\n| Component | File | Lines |\n|-----------|------|-------|\n| Domain Run type | `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | 40-57 |\n| CLI run command | `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | 163-221 |\n| CLI list command | `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | 262-350 |\n| Protobuf definitions | `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` | 25-121 |\n| SQLite store | `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | 134-277 |\n| RunStore interface | `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | 10-20 |\n| gRPC server | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | 90-458 |\n| Help text | `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` | 58-194 |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8f4ab27d3500ab8b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74266\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 130345</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f29cf043-1251-4213-84f2-becb34ef1768","uuid":"77ba52ff-8f13-4354-af4c-92c01bfe1aa6","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go codebase to understand:\n1. The `cloche run` command implementation - where flags are defined and how runs are created\n2. The `cloche list` command implementation - how output is formatted\n3. The domain types for Run - what fields exist\n4. The gRPC protobuf definitions for runs\n5. The SQLite store implementation for runs\n6. The ports/interfaces for RunStore\n\nBe very thorough - I need to see all relevant files for adding an \"issue ID\" field to runs and fixing table alignment in list output.","agentId":"a8f4ab27d3500ab8b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide a comprehensive analysis report.\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Codebase Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase to understand all the components needed for adding an \"issue ID\" field to runs and fixing table alignment in list output. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Domain Types for Run** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (194 lines)\n\nThe `Run` struct already has a `TaskID` field (line 56):\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n\tID             string\n\tWorkflowName   string\n\tState          RunState\n\tActiveSteps    []string\n\tStepExecutions []*StepExecution\n\tStartedAt      time.Time\n\tCompletedAt    time.Time\n\tProjectDir     string\n\tErrorMessage   string\n\tContainerID    string\n\tBaseSHA        string\n\tContainerKept  bool\n\tTitle          string\n\tIsHost         bool\n\tParentRunID    string\n\tTaskID         string 