{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A5Afxvs4mJTR31VLVHZG9j","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package main\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"fmt\"\n     5→\t\"os\"\n     6→)\n     7→\n     8→// subcommandHelp maps each subcommand to its detailed help text.\n     9→// Help text is formatted for LLM consumption: structured, explicit, with examples.\n    10→var subcommandHelp = map[string]string{\n    11→\t\"init\": `cloche init — Initialize a Cloche project\n    12→\n    13→Creates the .cloche/ directory with a workflow definition, Dockerfile,\n    14→prompt templates, and configuration files.\n    15→\n    16→Usage:\n    17→  cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n    18→\n    19→Flags:\n    20→  --workflow <name>       Name for the workflow file (default: \"develop\")\n    21→  --base-image <image>    Base Docker image for the Dockerfile (default: \"cloche-base:latest\")\n    22→\n    23→What it creates:\n    24→  .cloche/<name>.cloche           Workflow definition\n    25→  .cloche/host.cloche             Host orchestration workflow\n    26→  .cloche/Dockerfile              Container image definition\n    27→  .cloche/config.toml             Project configuration\n    28→  .cloche/prompts/implement.md    Prompt for the implement step\n    29→  .cloche/prompts/fix.md          Prompt for the fix step\n    30→  .cloche/prompts/update-docs.md  Prompt for the update-docs step\n    31→  .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh  Prompt generation script\n    32→  .cloche/version                 Schema version marker\n    33→\n    34→Existing files are never overwritten. Run this command again safely to add\n    35→missing files without losing customizations.\n    36→\n    37→Examples:\n    38→  cloche init\n    39→  cloche init --workflow build --base-image python:3.12\n    40→`,\n    41→\n    42→\t\"health\": `cloche health — Show project health summary\n    43→\n    44→Queries the daemon's HTTP API for a summary of all registered projects\n    45→and their pass/fail test counts.\n    46→\n    47→Usage:\n    48→  cloche health\n    49→\n    50→Environment:\n    51→  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (e.g. \"localhost:8080\"). Required.\n    52→\n    53→Examples:\n    54→  export CLOCHE_HTTP=localhost:8080\n    55→  cloche health\n    56→`,\n    57→\n    58→\t\"run\": `cloche run — Launch a workflow run\n    59→\n    60→Starts a new container workflow run. The daemon builds/pulls the container\n    61→image, copies the project into it, and executes the workflow steps.\n    62→\n    63→Usage:\n    64→  cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n    65→  cloche run <name>              (shorthand: bare positional workflow name)\n    66→\n    67→Flags:\n    68→  --workflow <name>    Name of the workflow to run (required). Must match a\n    69→                       .cloche/<name>.cloche file in the project.\n    70→  --prompt \"...\"       Prompt text passed to agent steps. Also available as\n    71→  -p \"...\"             the short form.\n    72→  --title \"...\"        Human-readable title for the run (shown in status/list).\n    73→  --keep-container     Do not remove the container after the run completes.\n    74→                       Useful for debugging.\n    75→\n    76→The command prints the run ID on success. Use that ID with status, logs,\n    77→poll, and stop.\n    78→\n    79→Examples:\n    80→  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add a /health endpoint\"\n    81→  cloche run develop -p \"Fix the broken CSV parser\" --title \"CSV fix\"\n    82→  cloche run --workflow build --keep-container\n    83→`,\n    84→\n    85→\t\"status\": `cloche status — Check run status\n    86→\n    87→Shows the current state of a workflow run including its type, active step,\n    88→and the result of each completed step.\n    89→\n    90→Usage:\n    91→  cloche status <run-id>\n    92→\n    93→Arguments:\n    94→  <run-id>    The run identifier returned by \"cloche run\".\n    95→\n    96→Output fields:\n    97→  Run         Run identifier\n    98→  Title       Human-readable title (if set)\n    99→  Workflow    Workflow name\n   100→  Type        \"host\" or \"container\"\n   101→  State       Current state (e.g. running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n   102→  Container   Truncated container ID (container runs only)\n   103→  Error       Error message (if failed)\n   104→  Active      Name of the currently executing step\n   105→  Steps       List of completed steps with results and timestamps\n   106→\n   107→Examples:\n   108→  cloche status abc123\n   109→`,\n   110→\n   111→\t\"logs\": `cloche logs — Show logs for a run\n   112→\n   113→Streams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\n   114→step name and log type, limiting output, and following live output.\n   115→\n   116→Usage:\n   117→  cloche logs <run-id> [-s <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n   118→\n   119→Arguments:\n   120→  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   121→\n   122→Flags:\n   123→  --step, -s <name>              Show logs only for the named step.\n   124→  --type <full|script|llm>       Filter by log type:\n   125→                                   full    — complete unfiltered output\n   126→                                   script  — script/command output only\n   127→                                   llm     — LLM interaction logs only\n   128→  --follow, -f                   Stream logs in real time (blocks until the\n   129→                                 run completes or is stopped).\n   130→  --limit, -l <n>                Display only the last n lines of output.\n   131→\n   132→Flags are combinable: cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f\n   133→\n   134→Examples:\n   135→  cloche logs abc123\n   136→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement\n   137→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20\n   138→  cloche logs abc123 -f\n   139→  cloche logs abc123 -s test --type script\n   140→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20 -f\n   141→`,\n   142→\n   143→\t\"poll\": `cloche poll — Wait for runs to finish\n   144→\n   145→Polls the daemon every 2 seconds until all runs reach a terminal state\n   146→(succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n   147→\n   148→With a single run ID, prints step-level progress (same as before).\n   149→With multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary.\n   150→\n   151→Usage:\n   152→  cloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n   153→\n   154→Arguments:\n   155→  <run-id>    One or more run identifiers.\n   156→\n   157→Exit codes:\n   158→  0    All runs succeeded.\n   159→  1    Any run failed, was cancelled, or the container died.\n   160→\n   161→Examples:\n   162→  cloche poll abc123\n   163→  cloche poll abc123 def456 ghi789\n   164→  cloche run develop -p \"Fix bug\" && cloche poll \"$(cloche run develop -p 'Fix bug')\"\n   165→`,\n   166→\n   167→\t\"list\": `cloche list — List workflow runs\n   168→\n   169→Shows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\n   170→with --all. Results can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited\n   171→to a fixed number.\n   172→\n   173→Usage:\n   174→  cloche list [flags]\n   175→\n   176→Flags:\n   177→  --all              Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n   178→  --project, -p DIR  Filter by project directory.\n   179→  --state, -s STATE  Filter by run state (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled).\n   180→  --limit, -n NUM    Limit the number of results returned.\n   181→  --issue, -i ID     Filter by issue/task ID.\n   182→\n   183→Output columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\n   184→title, container ID, and error message (if any).\n   185→\n   186→Examples:\n   187→  cloche list\n   188→  cloche list --all\n   189→  cloche list --state running\n   190→  cloche list --limit 10\n   191→  cloche list --all --state failed --limit 5\n   192→  cloche list --issue TASK-123\n   193→  cloche list -p /home/user/project -s succeeded -n 20\n   194→`,\n   195→\n   196→\t\"stop\": `cloche stop — Stop a running workflow\n   197→\n   198→Sends a stop signal to a running workflow. The container is terminated\n   199→and the run state transitions to \"cancelled\".\n   200→\n   201→Usage:\n   202→  cloche stop <run-id>\n   203→\n   204→Arguments:\n   205→  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   206→\n   207→Examples:\n   208→  cloche stop abc123\n   209→`,\n   210→\n   211→\t\"delete\": `cloche delete — Delete a retained container\n   212→\n   213→Removes a container that was kept after a run (via --keep-container).\n   214→Accepts either a container ID or a run ID.\n   215→\n   216→Usage:\n   217→  cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   218→\n   219→Arguments:\n   220→  <container-or-run-id>    Container ID or run ID to delete.\n   221→\n   222→Examples:\n   223→  cloche delete abc123\n   224→`,\n   225→\n   226→\t\"tasks\": `cloche tasks — Show task pipeline and assignment state\n   227→\n   228→Queries the daemon's HTTP API for the current task list, showing which\n   229→tasks are open, assigned, or completed.\n   230→\n   231→Usage:\n   232→  cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   233→\n   234→Flags:\n   235→  --project <dir>    Project directory name to query (default: current\n   236→                     directory basename).\n   237→\n   238→Environment:\n   239→  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (default: \"localhost:8080\").\n   240→\n   241→Output columns: ID, STATUS, ASSIGNED, RUN, TITLE\n   242→\n   243→Examples:\n   244→  cloche tasks\n   245→  cloche tasks --project my-app\n   246→`,\n   247→\n   248→\t\"loop\": `cloche loop — Manage the orchestration loop\n   249→\n   250→Starts, stops, or resumes the daemon's orchestration loop, which\n   251→automatically picks up and runs tasks from the task pipeline.\n   252→\n   253→Usage:\n   254→  cloche loop [--max <n>]     Start the orchestration loop\n   255→  cloche loop stop            Stop the orchestration loop\n   256→  cloche loop resume          Resume a halted loop (clear error state)\n   257→\n   258→Flags:\n   259→  --max <n>    Maximum number of concurrent runs (default: value from\n   260→               .cloche/config.toml).\n   261→\n   262→When stop_on_error is enabled in .cloche/config.toml, an unrecovered\n   263→error will halt the loop. Use \"cloche loop resume\" to clear the error\n   264→and resume picking up new work.\n   265→\n   266→Examples:\n   267→  cloche loop\n   268→  cloche loop --max 3\n   269→  cloche loop stop\n   270→  cloche loop resume\n   271→`,\n   272→\n   273→\t\"get\": `cloche get — Get a value from the run context store\n   274→\n   275→Reads a key from the run's context.json file. Intended for use inside\n   276→workflow scripts and steps.\n   277→\n   278→Usage:\n   279→  cloche get <key>\n   280→\n   281→Arguments:\n   282→  <key>    The context key to read.\n   283→\n   284→Environment:\n   285→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n   286→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n   287→\n   288→Exit codes:\n   289→  0    Key exists; value printed to stdout.\n   290→  1    Key not found or error.\n   291→\n   292→Examples:\n   293→  cloche get branch\n   294→  cloche get task_id\n   295→`,\n   296→\n   297→\t\"set\": `cloche set — Set a value in the run context store\n   298→\n   299→Writes a key-value pair to the run's context.json file. Use \"-\" as the\n   300→value to read from stdin (useful for multi-line content).\n   301→\n   302→Usage:\n   303→  cloche set <key> <value>\n   304→  cloche set <key> -          (read value from stdin)\n   305→\n   306→Arguments:\n   307→  <key>      The context key to write.\n   308→  <value>    The value to store, or \"-\" to read from stdin.\n   309→\n   310→Environment:\n   311→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n   312→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n   313→\n   314→Examples:\n   315→  cloche set branch feature-auth\n   316→  echo \"multi-line content\" | cloche set notes -\n   317→`,\n   318→\n   319→\t\"workflow\": `cloche workflow — View workflow definitions\n   320→\n   321→Lists all workflows in the project or renders a specific workflow as an\n   322→ASCII-art graph showing steps, wiring, and result paths.\n   323→\n   324→Usage:\n   325→  cloche workflow [--project <dir>]          List all workflows\n   326→  cloche workflow <name> [--project <dir>]   Show workflow graph\n   327→\n   328→Arguments:\n   329→  <name>    Name of the workflow to render as a graph.\n   330→\n   331→Flags:\n   332→  --project <dir>, -p <dir>    Project directory (default: current directory).\n   333→\n   334→When listing, workflows are grouped by type (container or host). When\n   335→showing a specific workflow, the output is a graph with step boxes and\n   336→colored wires: green for success, red for fail/failed, and\n   337→blue/yellow/orange/magenta for other result paths. Wires to the same\n   338→destination are merged for readability.\n   339→\n   340→Examples:\n   341→  cloche workflow\n   342→  cloche workflow develop\n   343→  cloche workflow main -p /path/to/project\n   344→  cloche workflow --project ../other-project\n   345→`,\n   346→\n   347→\t\"project\": `cloche project — Show project info and config\n   348→\n   349→Displays project-level information including config settings, orchestrator\n   350→loop state, concurrency, active runs, and known workflows.\n   351→\n   352→By default, looks up the project by the current working directory. Use\n   353→--name to look up a project by its label instead.\n   354→\n   355→Usage:\n   356→  cloche project [--name <label>]\n   357→\n   358→Flags:\n   359→  --name <label>    Look up project by label (e.g. \"cloche\") instead of\n   360→                    the current directory.\n   361→\n   362→Output includes:\n   363→  Config            active, concurrency, stagger, dedup, stop_on_error,\n   364→                    evolution settings\n   365→  Loop              Orchestration loop state (running, stopped, or halted)\n   366→  Active runs       Currently pending or running workflow runs\n   367→  Workflows         Known container and host workflow names\n   368→\n   369→Environment:\n   370→  CLOCHE_ADDR    Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n   371→\n   372→Examples:\n   373→  cloche project\n   374→  cloche project --name cloche\n   375→  cloche project --name my-app\n   376→`,\n   377→\n   378→\t\"validate\": `cloche validate — Validate project configuration and workflows\n   379→\n   380→Parses and validates all config and workflow files in the project's .cloche/\n   381→directory. Checks syntax, result wiring, terminal coverage, orphan steps,\n   382→file references, and cross-file consistency.\n   383→\n   384→Usage:\n   385→  cloche validate [--project <path>] [--workflow <name>]\n   386→\n   387→Flags:\n   388→  --project <path>    Project directory to validate (default: current directory).\n   389→  --workflow <name>   Validate only the named workflow instead of all workflows.\n   390→\n   391→Checks performed:\n   392→  config.toml         Parses correctly, fields are valid.\n   393→  Workflow files      Syntax, result wiring completeness, terminal coverage\n   394→                      (all paths reach done/abort), no orphan steps, and\n   395→                      config key validation.\n   396→  File references     prompt file() paths resolve to .cloche/prompts/,\n   397→                      script run paths resolve to .cloche/scripts/.\n   398→  Cross-file          workflow_name references resolve to defined workflows.\n   399→\n   400→Exit codes:\n   401→  0    All configuration valid.\n   402→  1    One or more errors found.\n   403→\n   404→Examples:\n   405→  cloche validate\n   406→  cloche validate --project /path/to/project\n   407→  cloche validate --workflow develop\n   408→`,\n   409→\n   410→\t\"shutdown\": `cloche shutdown — Shut down the daemon\n   411→\n   412→Sends a shutdown signal to the Cloche daemon. Refuses to shut down if\n   413→there are active runs unless --force is specified.\n   414→\n   415→Usage:\n   416→  cloche shutdown [--force|-f]\n   417→\n   418→Flags:\n   419→  -f, --force   Shut down even if runs are still active.\n   420→\n   421→Examples:\n   422→  cloche shutdown\n   423→  cloche shutdown --force\n   424→`,\n   425→}\n   426→\n   427→// printHelp prints the top-level help or subcommand-specific help.\n   428→// Returns true if help was printed (caller should exit).\n   429→func printHelp(args []string) bool {\n   430→\tif len(args) == 0 {\n   431→\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   432→\t\treturn true\n   433→\t}\n   434→\n   435→\t// \"cloche help <subcommand>\"\n   436→\tcmd := args[0]\n   437→\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n   438→\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n   439→\t\treturn true\n   440→\t}\n   441→\n   442→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"unknown command: %s\\n\\n\", cmd)\n   443→\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   444→\treturn true\n   445→}\n   446→\n   447→// hasHelpFlag returns true if the args contain --help or -h.\n   448→func hasHelpFlag(args []string) bool {\n   449→\tfor _, arg := range args {\n   450→\t\tif arg == \"--help\" || arg == \"-h\" {\n   451→\t\t\treturn true\n   452→\t\t}\n   453→\t}\n   454→\treturn false\n   455→}\n   456→\n   457→// printSubcommandHelp prints help for a subcommand and exits.\n   458→func printSubcommandHelp(cmd string) {\n   459→\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n   460→\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n   461→\t} else {\n   462→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"no help available for %q\\n\", cmd)\n   463→\t}\n   464→}\n   465→\n   466→func printTopLevelHelp() {\n   467→\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, `cloche — Grow-code high quality applications\n   468→\n   469→Cloche provides containerized environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL\n   470→for linking agentic and script-driven tasks, and validated code pipelines.\n   471→\n   472→Usage:\n   473→  cloche <command> [args]\n   474→  cloche help <command>       Show detailed help for a command\n   475→  cloche <command> --help     Same as above\n   476→\n   477→Project Setup:\n   478→  init       Initialize a Cloche project (.cloche/ directory and templates)\n   479→  health     Show project health summary (pass/fail counts)\n   480→  project    Show project info, config, loop state, and workflows\n   481→\n   482→Workflow Info:\n   483→  workflow   List workflows or show a workflow as an ASCII-art graph\n   484→  validate   Validate project configuration and workflow definitions\n   485→\n   486→Workflow Runs:\n   487→  run        Launch a workflow run in a container\n   488→  status     Check run status (state, steps, errors)\n   489→  logs       Show or stream logs for a run\n   490→  poll       Wait for one or more runs to finish (blocks until terminal)\n   491→  list       List runs for current project (or all projects)\n   492→  stop       Stop a running workflow\n   493→  delete     Delete a retained container\n   494→\n   495→Orchestration:\n   496→  tasks      Show task pipeline and assignment state\n   497→  loop       Start or stop the orchestration loop\n   498→\n   499→Context Store (for use inside workflow steps):\n   500→  get        Get a value from the run context store\n   501→  set        Set a value in the run context store\n   502→\n   503→Daemon:\n   504→  shutdown   Shut down the Cloche daemon\n   505→\n   506→Environment Variables:\n   507→  CLOCHE_ADDR          Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n   508→  CLOCHE_HTTP          Daemon HTTP address (for health/tasks commands)\n   509→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run ID for get/set commands (set automatically in steps)\n   510→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory override for get/set commands\n   511→\n   512→Examples:\n   513→  cloche init\n   514→  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add user authentication\"\n   515→  cloche status abc123\n   516→  cloche logs abc123 --follow\n   517→  cloche list\n   518→  cloche loop --max 2\n   519→`)\n   520→}\n   521→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f29cf043-1251-4213-84f2-becb34ef1768","uuid":"5419337a-4237-4f23-a539-705c7538188b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go","content":"package main\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n)\n\n// subcommandHelp maps each subcommand to its detailed help text.\n// Help text is formatted for LLM consumption: structured, explicit, with examples.\nvar subcommandHelp = map[string]string{\n\t\"init\": `cloche init — Initialize a Cloche project\n\nCreates the .cloche/ directory with a workflow definition, Dockerfile,\nprompt templates, and configuration files.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n\nFlags:\n  --workflow <name>       Name for the workflow file (default: \"develop\")\n  --base-image <image>    Base Docker image for the Dockerfile (default: \"cloche-base:latest\")\n\nWhat it creates:\n  .cloche/<name>.cloche           Workflow definition\n  .cloche/host.cloche             Host orchestration workflow\n  .cloche/Dockerfile              Container image definition\n  .cloche/config.toml             Project configuration\n  .cloche/prompts/implement.md    Prompt for the implement step\n  .cloche/prompts/fix.md          Prompt for the fix step\n  .cloche/prompts/update-docs.md  Prompt for the update-docs step\n  .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh  Prompt generation script\n  .cloche/version                 Schema version marker\n\nExisting files are never overwritten. Run this command again safely to add\nmissing files without losing customizations.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche init\n  cloche init --workflow build --base-image python:3.12\n`,\n\n\t\"health\": `cloche health — Show project health summary\n\nQueries the daemon's HTTP API for a summary of all registered projects\nand their pass/fail test counts.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche health\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (e.g. \"localhost:8080\"). Required.\n\nExamples:\n  export CLOCHE_HTTP=localhost:8080\n  cloche health\n`,\n\n\t\"run\": `cloche run — Launch a workflow run\n\nStarts a new container workflow run. The daemon builds/pulls the container\nimage, copies the project into it, and executes the workflow steps.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n  cloche run <name>              (shorthand: bare positional workflow name)\n\nFlags:\n  --workflow <name>    Name of the workflow to run (required). Must match a\n                       .cloche/<name>.cloche file in the project.\n  --prompt \"...\"       Prompt text passed to agent steps. Also available as\n  -p \"...\"             the short form.\n  --title \"...\"        Human-readable title for the run (shown in status/list).\n  --keep-container     Do not remove the container after the run completes.\n                       Useful for debugging.\n\nThe command prints the run ID on success. Use that ID with status, logs,\npoll, and stop.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add a /health endpoint\"\n  cloche run develop -p \"Fix the broken CSV parser\" --title \"CSV fix\"\n  cloche run --workflow build --keep-container\n`,\n\n\t\"status\": `cloche status — Check run status\n\nShows the current state of a workflow run including its type, active step,\nand the result of each completed step.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche status <run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier returned by \"cloche run\".\n\nOutput fields:\n  Run         Run identifier\n  Title       Human-readable title (if set)\n  Workflow    Workflow name\n  Type        \"host\" or \"container\"\n  State       Current state (e.g. running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n  Container   Truncated container ID (container runs only)\n  Error       Error message (if failed)\n  Active      Name of the currently executing step\n  Steps       List of completed steps with results and timestamps\n\nExamples:\n  cloche status abc123\n`,\n\n\t\"logs\": `cloche logs — Show logs for a run\n\nStreams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\nstep name and log type, limiting output, and following live output.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche logs <run-id> [-s <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n\nFlags:\n  --step, -s <name>              Show logs only for the named step.\n  --type <full|script|llm>       Filter by log type:\n                                   full    — complete unfiltered output\n                                   script  — script/command output only\n                                   llm     — LLM interaction logs only\n  --follow, -f                   Stream logs in real time (blocks until the\n                                 run completes or is stopped).\n  --limit, -l <n>                Display only the last n lines of output.\n\nFlags are combinable: cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f\n\nExamples:\n  cloche logs abc123\n  cloche logs abc123 -s implement\n  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20\n  cloche logs abc123 -f\n  cloche logs abc123 -s test --type script\n  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20 -f\n`,\n\n\t\"poll\": `cloche poll — Wait for runs to finish\n\nPolls the daemon every 2 seconds until all runs reach a terminal state\n(succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n\nWith a single run ID, prints step-level progress (same as before).\nWith multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    One or more run identifiers.\n\nExit codes:\n  0    All runs succeeded.\n  1    Any run failed, was cancelled, or the container died.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche poll abc123\n  cloche poll abc123 def456 ghi789\n  cloche run develop -p \"Fix bug\" && cloche poll \"$(cloche run develop -p 'Fix bug')\"\n`,\n\n\t\"list\": `cloche list — List workflow runs\n\nShows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\nwith --all. Results can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited\nto a fixed number.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche list [flags]\n\nFlags:\n  --all              Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n  --project, -p DIR  Filter by project directory.\n  --state, -s STATE  Filter by run state (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled).\n  --limit, -n NUM    Limit the number of results returned.\n  --issue, -i ID     Filter by issue/task ID.\n\nOutput columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\ntitle, container ID, and error message (if any).\n\nExamples:\n  cloche list\n  cloche list --all\n  cloche list --state running\n  cloche list --limit 10\n  cloche list --all --state failed --limit 5\n  cloche list --issue TASK-123\n  cloche list -p /home/user/project -s succeeded -n 20\n`,\n\n\t\"stop\": `cloche stop — Stop a running workflow\n\nSends a stop signal to a running workflow. The container is terminated\nand the run state transitions to \"cancelled\".\n\nUsage:\n  cloche stop <run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche stop abc123\n`,\n\n\t\"delete\": `cloche delete — Delete a retained container\n\nRemoves a container that was kept after a run (via --keep-container).\nAccepts either a container ID or a run ID.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <container-or-run-id>    Container ID or run ID to delete.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche delete abc123\n`,\n\n\t\"tasks\": `cloche tasks — Show task pipeline and assignment state\n\nQueries the daemon's HTTP API for the current task list, showing which\ntasks are open, assigned, or completed.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n\nFlags:\n  --project <dir>    Project directory name to query (default: current\n                     directory basename).\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (default: \"localhost:8080\").\n\nOutput columns: ID, STATUS, ASSIGNED, RUN, TITLE\n\nExamples:\n  cloche tasks\n  cloche tasks --project my-app\n`,\n\n\t\"loop\": `cloche loop — Manage the orchestration loop\n\nStarts, stops, or resumes the daemon's orchestration loop, which\nautomatically picks up and runs tasks from the task pipeline.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche loop [--max <n>]     Start the orchestration loop\n  cloche loop stop            Stop the orchestration loop\n  cloche loop resume          Resume a halted loop (clear error state)\n\nFlags:\n  --max <n>    Maximum number of concurrent runs (default: value from\n               .cloche/config.toml).\n\nWhen stop_on_error is enabled in .cloche/config.toml, an unrecovered\nerror will halt the loop. Use \"cloche loop resume\" to clear the error\nand resume picking up new work.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche loop\n  cloche loop --max 3\n  cloche loop stop\n  cloche loop resume\n`,\n\n\t\"get\": `cloche get — Get a value from the run context store\n\nReads a key from the run's context.json file. Intended for use inside\nworkflow scripts and steps.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche get <key>\n\nArguments:\n  <key>    The context key to read.\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n\nExit codes:\n  0    Key exists; value printed to stdout.\n  1    Key not found or error.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche get branch\n  cloche get task_id\n`,\n\n\t\"set\": `cloche set — Set a value in the run context store\n\nWrites a key-value pair to the run's context.json file. Use \"-\" as the\nvalue to read from stdin (useful for multi-line content).\n\nUsage:\n  cloche set <key> <value>\n  cloche set <key> -          (read value from stdin)\n\nArguments:\n  <key>      The context key to write.\n  <value>    The value to store, or \"-\" to read from stdin.\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n\nExamples:\n  cloche set branch feature-auth\n  echo \"multi-line content\" | cloche set notes -\n`,\n\n\t\"workflow\": `cloche workflow — View workflow definitions\n\nLists all workflows in the project or renders a specific workflow as an\nASCII-art graph showing steps, wiring, and result paths.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche workflow [--project <dir>]          List all workflows\n  cloche workflow <name> [--project <dir>]   Show workflow graph\n\nArguments:\n  <name>    Name of the workflow to render as a graph.\n\nFlags:\n  --project <dir>, -p <dir>    Project directory (default: current directory).\n\nWhen listing, workflows are grouped by type (container or host). When\nshowing a specific workflow, the output is a graph with step boxes and\ncolored wires: green for success, red for fail/failed, and\nblue/yellow/orange/magenta for other result paths. Wires to the same\ndestination are merged for readability.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche workflow\n  cloche workflow develop\n  cloche workflow main -p /path/to/project\n  cloche workflow --project ../other-project\n`,\n\n\t\"project\": `cloche project — Show project info and config\n\nDisplays project-level information including config settings, orchestrator\nloop state, concurrency, active runs, and known workflows.\n\nBy default, looks up the project by the current working directory. Use\n--name to look up a project by its label instead.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche project [--name <label>]\n\nFlags:\n  --name <label>    Look up project by label (e.g. \"cloche\") instead of\n                    the current directory.\n\nOutput includes:\n  Config            active, concurrency, stagger, dedup, stop_on_error,\n                    evolution settings\n  Loop              Orchestration loop state (running, stopped, or halted)\n  Active runs       Currently pending or running workflow runs\n  Workflows         Known container and host workflow names\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_ADDR    Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n\nExamples:\n  cloche project\n  cloche project --name cloche\n  cloche project --name my-app\n`,\n\n\t\"validate\": `cloche validate — Validate project configuration and workflows\n\nParses and validates all config and workflow files in the project's .cloche/\ndirectory. Checks syntax, result wiring, terminal coverage, orphan steps,\nfile references, and cross-file consistency.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche validate [--project <path>] [--workflow <name>]\n\nFlags:\n  --project <path>    Project directory to validate (default: current directory).\n  --workflow <name>   Validate only the named workflow instead of all workflows.\n\nChecks performed:\n  config.toml         Parses correctly, fields are valid.\n  Workflow files      Syntax, result wiring completeness, terminal coverage\n                      (all paths reach done/abort), no orphan steps, and\n                      config key validation.\n  File references     prompt file() paths resolve to .cloche/prompts/,\n                      script run paths resolve to .cloche/scripts/.\n  Cross-file          workflow_name references resolve to defined workflows.\n\nExit codes:\n  0    All configuration valid.\n  1    One or more errors found.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche validate\n  cloche validate --project /path/to/project\n  cloche validate --workflow develop\n`,\n\n\t\"shutdown\": `cloche shutdown — Shut down the daemon\n\nSends a shutdown signal to the Cloche daemon. Refuses to shut down if\nthere are active runs unless --force is specified.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche shutdown [--force|-f]\n\nFlags:\n  -f, --force   Shut down even if runs are still active.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche shutdown\n  cloche shutdown --force\n`,\n}\n\n// printHelp prints the top-level help or subcommand-specific help.\n// Returns true if help was printed (caller should exit).\nfunc printHelp(args []string) bool {\n\tif len(args) == 0 {\n\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n\n\t// \"cloche help <subcommand>\"\n\tcmd := args[0]\n\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n\n\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"unknown command: %s\\n\\n\", cmd)\n\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n\treturn true\n}\n\n// hasHelpFlag returns true if the args contain --help or -h.\nfunc hasHelpFlag(args []string) bool {\n\tfor _, arg := range args {\n\t\tif arg == \"--help\" || arg == \"-h\" {\n\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn false\n}\n\n// printSubcommandHelp prints help for a subcommand and exits.\nfunc printSubcommandHelp(cmd string) {\n\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n\t} else {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"no help available for %q\\n\", cmd)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc printTopLevelHelp() {\n\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, `cloche — Grow-code high quality applications\n\nCloche provides containerized environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL\nfor linking agentic and script-driven tasks, and validated code pipelines.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche <command> [args]\n  cloche help <command>       Show detailed help for a command\n  cloche <command> --help     Same as above\n\nProject Setup:\n  init       Initialize a Cloche project (.cloche/ directory and templates)\n  health     Show project health summary (pass/fail counts)\n  project    Show project info, config, loop state, and workflows\n\nWorkflow Info:\n  workflow   List workflows or show a workflow as an ASCII-art graph\n  validate   Validate project configuration and workflow definitions\n\nWorkflow Runs:\n  run        Launch a workflow run in a container\n  status     Check run status (state, steps, errors)\n  logs       Show or stream logs for a run\n  poll       Wait for one or more runs to finish (blocks until terminal)\n  list       List runs for current project (or all projects)\n  stop       Stop a running workflow\n  delete     Delete a retained container\n\nOrchestration:\n  tasks      Show task pipeline and assignment state\n  loop       Start or stop the orchestration loop\n\nContext Store (for use inside workflow steps):\n  get        Get a value from the run context store\n  set        Set a value in the run context store\n\nDaemon:\n  shutdown   Shut down the Cloche daemon\n\nEnvironment Variables:\n  CLOCHE_ADDR          Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n  CLOCHE_HTTP          Daemon HTTP address (for health/tasks commands)\n  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run ID for get/set commands (set automatically in steps)\n  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory override for get/set commands\n\nExamples:\n  cloche init\n  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add user authentication\"\n  cloche status abc123\n  cloche logs abc123 --follow\n  cloche list\n  cloche loop --max 2\n`)\n}\n","numLines":521,"startLine":1,"totalLines":521}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XBnQU6GDSKjmfqfTgYhwkF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package grpc\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bufio\"\n     5→\t\"context\"\n     6→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     7→\t\"fmt\"\n     8→\t\"log\"\n     9→\t\"os\"\n    10→\t\"os/exec\"\n    11→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    12→\t\"sort\"\n    13→\t\"strconv\"\n    14→\t\"strings\"\n    15→\t\"sync\"\n    16→\t\"time\"\n    17→\n    18→\tpb \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb\"\n    19→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/docker\"\n    20→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/web\"\n    21→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/config\"\n    22→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    23→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n    24→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/evolution\"\n    25→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/host\"\n    26→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n    27→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    28→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n    29→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/version\"\n    30→\trpcgrpc \"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n    31→\t\"google.golang.org/grpc/metadata\"\n    32→)\n    33→\n    34→type ClocheServer struct {\n    35→\tpb.UnimplementedClocheServiceServer\n    36→\tstore        ports.RunStore\n    37→\tcaptures     ports.CaptureStore\n    38→\tlogStore     ports.LogStore\n    39→\tcontainer    ports.ContainerRuntime\n    40→\tdefaultImage string\n    41→\tevolution    *evolution.Trigger\n    42→\tlogBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    43→\tshutdownFn   func()\n    44→\tmu           sync.Mutex\n    45→\trunIDs       map[string]string      // run_id -> container_id\n    46→\tloops        map[string]*host.Loop  // project_dir -> orchestration loop\n    47→}\n    48→\n    49→func NewClocheServer(store ports.RunStore, container ports.ContainerRuntime) *ClocheServer {\n    50→\treturn &ClocheServer{\n    51→\t\tstore:     store,\n    52→\t\tcontainer: container,\n    53→\t\trunIDs:    make(map[string]string),\n    54→\t\tloops:     make(map[string]*host.Loop),\n    55→\t}\n    56→}\n    57→\n    58→func NewClocheServerWithCaptures(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, container ports.ContainerRuntime, defaultImage string) *ClocheServer {\n    59→\treturn &ClocheServer{\n    60→\t\tstore:        store,\n    61→\t\tcaptures:     captures,\n    62→\t\tcontainer:    container,\n    63→\t\tdefaultImage: defaultImage,\n    64→\t\trunIDs:       make(map[string]string),\n    65→\t\tloops:        make(map[string]*host.Loop),\n    66→\t}\n    67→}\n    68→\n    69→// SetLogStore attaches a log store to the server for indexing extracted log files.\n    70→func (s *ClocheServer) SetLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) {\n    71→\ts.logStore = ls\n    72→}\n    73→\n    74→\n    75→// SetEvolution attaches an evolution trigger to the server.\n    76→func (s *ClocheServer) SetEvolution(trigger *evolution.Trigger) {\n    77→\ts.evolution = trigger\n    78→}\n    79→\n    80→// SetLogBroadcaster attaches a log broadcaster for live-streaming LLM output.\n    81→func (s *ClocheServer) SetLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) {\n    82→\ts.logBroadcast = b\n    83→}\n    84→\n    85→// SetShutdownFunc sets the callback invoked when the Shutdown RPC is called.\n    86→func (s *ClocheServer) SetShutdownFunc(fn func()) {\n    87→\ts.shutdownFn = fn\n    88→}\n    89→\n    90→func (s *ClocheServer) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n    91→\t// Check if this is a host workflow (has host {} block).\n    92→\tif hostWFs, err := host.FindHostWorkflows(req.ProjectDir); err == nil {\n    93→\t\tif _, isHost := hostWFs[req.WorkflowName]; isHost {\n    94→\t\t\treturn s.runHostWorkflow(ctx, req)\n    95→\t\t}\n    96→\t}\n    97→\n    98→\tif s.container == nil {\n    99→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n   100→\t}\n   101→\n   102→\t// Generate a unique run ID, retrying on collision\n   103→\tvar runID string\n   104→\tfor attempts := 0; attempts < 10; attempts++ {\n   105→\t\trunID = domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n   106→\t\texisting, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   107→\t\tif err != nil {\n   108→\t\t\tbreak // ID is free\n   109→\t\t}\n   110→\t\t// Reuse if completed more than 1 hour ago\n   111→\t\tif !existing.CompletedAt.IsZero() && time.Since(existing.CompletedAt) > time.Hour {\n   112→\t\t\t_ = s.store.DeleteRun(ctx, runID)\n   113→\t\t\tbreak\n   114→\t\t}\n   115→\t}\n   116→\n   117→\t// Write prompt to .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt (run-specific to avoid conflicts)\n   118→\tif req.Prompt != \"\" {\n   119→\t\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(req.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID)\n   120→\t\tif err := os.MkdirAll(clocheDir, 0755); err != nil {\n   121→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating .cloche dir: %w\", err)\n   122→\t\t}\n   123→\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"prompt.txt\"), []byte(req.Prompt), 0644); err != nil {\n   124→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"writing prompt: %w\", err)\n   125→\t\t}\n   126→\t}\n   127→\trun := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\n   128→\trun.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\n   129→\trun.Title = req.Title\n   130→\tif err := s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run); err != nil {\n   131→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating run: %w\", err)\n   132→\t}\n   133→\n   134→\t// Resolve image: request-level override, then server default\n   135→\timage := req.Image\n   136→\tif image == \"\" {\n   137→\t\timage = s.defaultImage\n   138→\t}\n   139→\n   140→\t// Launch container start + tracking in background so the RPC returns immediately.\n   141→\t// The run stays in \"pending\" state until the container is up.\n   142→\tgo s.launchAndTrack(runID, image, req.KeepContainer, req)\n   143→\n   144→\treturn &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n   145→}\n   146→\n   147→// runHostWorkflow dispatches a host workflow via the host runner, returning\n   148→// immediately while the workflow runs in a background goroutine.\n   149→func (s *ClocheServer) runHostWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n   150→\trunID := domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n   151→\n   152→\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   153→\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   154→\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   155→\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   156→\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   157→\t}\n   158→\n   159→\tgo func() {\n   160→\t\trunner.RunNamedWithID(context.Background(), req.ProjectDir, req.WorkflowName, runID)\n   161→\t}()\n   162→\n   163→\treturn &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n   164→}\n   165→\n   166→// launchAndTrack starts the container and then tracks it to completion.\n   167→// It runs in a background goroutine with its own context, independent of the\n   168→// RPC context which may be cancelled after RunWorkflow returns.\n   169→func (s *ClocheServer) launchAndTrack(runID, image string, keepContainer bool, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) {\n   170→\tctx := context.Background()\n   171→\n   172→\t// Auto-rebuild image if the project Dockerfile has changed since last build.\n   173→\tif ensurer, ok := s.container.(ports.ImageEnsurer); ok {\n   174→\t\tif err := ensurer.EnsureImage(ctx, req.ProjectDir, image); err != nil {\n   175→\t\t\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   176→\t\t\tif run != nil {\n   177→\t\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to ensure image: %v\", err))\n   178→\t\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   179→\t\t\t}\n   180→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to ensure image: %v\", runID, err)\n   181→\t\t\t\treturn\n   182→\t\t}\n   183→\t}\n   184→\n   185→\tbaseSHA := gitHEAD(req.ProjectDir)\n   186→\n   187→\tcontainerID, err := s.container.Start(ctx, ports.ContainerConfig{\n   188→\t\tImage:        image,\n   189→\t\tWorkflowName: req.WorkflowName,\n   190→\t\tProjectDir:   req.ProjectDir,\n   191→\t\tRunID:        runID,\n   192→\t\tNetworkAllow: []string{\"*\"},\n   193→\t})\n   194→\tif err != nil {\n   195→\t\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   196→\t\tif run != nil {\n   197→\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to start container: %v\", err))\n   198→\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   199→\t\t}\n   200→\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to start container: %v\", runID, err)\n   201→\t\treturn\n   202→\t}\n   203→\n   204→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   205→\ts.runIDs[runID] = containerID\n   206→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   207→\n   208→\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   209→\tif run != nil {\n   210→\t\trun.Start()\n   211→\t\trun.ContainerID = containerID\n   212→\t\trun.BaseSHA = baseSHA\n   213→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   214→\t}\n   215→\n   216→\ts.trackRun(runID, containerID, req.ProjectDir, req.WorkflowName, keepContainer)\n   217→}\n   218→\n   219→func (s *ClocheServer) trackRun(runID, containerID, projectDir, workflowName string, keepContainer bool) {\n   220→\tctx := context.Background()\n   221→\n   222→\t// Attach to agent output\n   223→\treader, err := s.container.AttachOutput(ctx, containerID)\n   224→\tif err != nil {\n   225→\t\tlog.Printf(\"failed to attach to output for run %s: %v\", runID, err)\n   226→\t\t\treturn\n   227→\t}\n   228→\n   229→\t// Parse JSON-lines status messages\n   230→\tvar reportedResult string // captured from MsgRunCompleted, persisted after branch extraction\n   231→\tvar reportedError string  // captured from MsgError, used to set ErrorMessage on failed runs\n   232→\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(reader)\n   233→\tscanner.Buffer(make([]byte, 0, 256*1024), 1024*1024) // 1MB max to handle large log messages\n   234→\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n   235→\t\tvar msg protocol.StatusMessage\n   236→\t\tif err := json.Unmarshal(scanner.Bytes(), &msg); err != nil {\n   237→\t\t\tcontinue\n   238→\t\t}\n   239→\n   240→\t\t// Fast path: log messages don't need store interaction.\n   241→\t\tif msg.Type == protocol.MsgLog {\n   242→\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   243→\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   244→\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   245→\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"llm\",\n   246→\t\t\t\t\tContent:   msg.Message,\n   247→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   248→\t\t\t\t})\n   249→\t\t\t}\n   250→\t\t\tcontinue\n   251→\t\t}\n   252→\n   253→\t\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   254→\t\tif err != nil {\n   255→\t\t\tcontinue\n   256→\t\t}\n   257→\n   258→\t\tswitch msg.Type {\n   259→\t\tcase protocol.MsgStepStarted:\n   260→\t\t\trun.RecordStepStart(msg.StepName)\n   261→\t\t\tif s.captures != nil {\n   262→\t\t\t\t_ = s.captures.SaveCapture(ctx, runID, &domain.StepExecution{\n   263→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   264→\t\t\t\t\tStartedAt: msg.Timestamp,\n   265→\t\t\t\t})\n   266→\t\t\t}\n   267→\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   268→\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   269→\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   270→\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"status\",\n   271→\t\t\t\t\tContent:   \"step_started: \" + msg.StepName,\n   272→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   273→\t\t\t\t})\n   274→\t\t\t}\n   275→\t\tcase protocol.MsgStepCompleted:\n   276→\t\t\trun.RecordStepComplete(msg.StepName, msg.Result)\n   277→\t\t\tif s.captures != nil {\n   278→\t\t\t\t_ = s.captures.SaveCapture(ctx, runID, &domain.StepExecution{\n   279→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:    msg.StepName,\n   280→\t\t\t\t\tResult:      msg.Result,\n   281→\t\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: msg.Timestamp,\n   282→\t\t\t\t})\n   283→\t\t\t}\n   284→\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   285→\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   286→\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   287→\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"status\",\n   288→\t\t\t\t\tContent:   \"step_completed: \" + msg.StepName + \" -> \" + msg.Result,\n   289→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   290→\t\t\t\t})\n   291→\t\t\t}\n   292→\t\tcase protocol.MsgRunTitle:\n   293→\t\t\tif run.Title == \"\" {\n   294→\t\t\t\trun.Title = msg.Message\n   295→\t\t\t}\n   296→\t\tcase protocol.MsgError:\n   297→\t\t\treportedError = msg.Message\n   298→\t\t\tcontinue // Don't persist; used during finalization\n   299→\t\tcase protocol.MsgRunCompleted:\n   300→\t\t\treportedResult = msg.Result\n   301→\t\t\tcontinue // Don't persist terminal state yet; branch extraction must finish first\n   302→\t\t}\n   303→\n   304→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   305→\t}\n   306→\treader.Close()\n   307→\n   308→\t// Signal live-stream subscribers that this run is done.\n   309→\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   310→\t\ts.logBroadcast.Finish(runID)\n   311→\t}\n   312→\n   313→\t// Wait for process exit\n   314→\texitCode, err := s.container.Wait(ctx, containerID)\n   315→\tif err != nil {\n   316→\t\tlog.Printf(\"error waiting for run %s: %v\", runID, err)\n   317→\t}\n   318→\n   319→\t// Extract step output files from container before it's removed\n   320→\toutputDst := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"output\")\n   321→\tif err := os.MkdirAll(outputDst, 0755); err == nil {\n   322→\t\tif cpErr := s.container.CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, \"/workspace/.cloche/output/.\", outputDst); cpErr != nil {\n   323→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to extract output: %v\", runID, cpErr)\n   324→\t\t}\n   325→\t}\n   326→\n   327→\t// Capture full container stdout/stderr before the container is removed\n   328→\tif logs, logErr := s.container.Logs(ctx, containerID); logErr == nil && logs != \"\" {\n   329→\t\tcontainerLogPath := filepath.Join(outputDst, \"container.log\")\n   330→\t\tif writeErr := os.WriteFile(containerLogPath, []byte(logs), 0644); writeErr != nil {\n   331→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to write container.log: %v\", runID, writeErr)\n   332→\t\t}\n   333→\t}\n   334→\n   335→\t// Index extracted log files in the log store\n   336→\tif s.logStore != nil {\n   337→\t\ts.indexLogFiles(ctx, runID, outputDst)\n   338→\t}\n   339→\n   340→\t// Extract results to git branch BEFORE finalizing state, so that\n   341→\t// WaitRun callers (e.g. host workflow merge step) see branches exist\n   342→\t// before the run is marked complete.\n   343→\tresultLabel := reportedResult\n   344→\tif resultLabel == \"\" {\n   345→\t\tif exitCode == 0 {\n   346→\t\t\tresultLabel = \"succeeded\"\n   347→\t\t} else {\n   348→\t\t\tresultLabel = \"failed\"\n   349→\t\t}\n   350→\t}\n   351→\t{\n   352→\t\textractRun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   353→\t\tif extractRun != nil && extractRun.BaseSHA != \"\" {\n   354→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: extracting results to branch cloche/%s (baseSHA=%s)\", runID, runID, extractRun.BaseSHA)\n   355→\t\t\tif err := docker.ExtractResults(ctx, containerID, extractRun.ProjectDir, runID, extractRun.BaseSHA, workflowName, resultLabel); err != nil {\n   356→\t\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to extract results to branch: %v\", runID, err)\n   357→\t\t\t} else {\n   358→\t\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: branch cloche/%s created successfully\", runID, runID)\n   359→\t\t\t}\n   360→\t\t} else {\n   361→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: skipping branch extraction (baseSHA empty or run not found)\", runID)\n   362→\t\t}\n   363→\t}\n   364→\n   365→\t// Now finalize run state\n   366→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   367→\tif err != nil {\n   368→\t\treturn\n   369→\t}\n   370→\tif run.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n   371→\t\tif reportedResult == \"succeeded\" {\n   372→\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   373→\t\t} else if reportedResult != \"\" {\n   374→\t\t\tif reportedError != \"\" {\n   375→\t\t\t\trun.Fail(reportedError)\n   376→\t\t\t} else {\n   377→\t\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n   378→\t\t\t}\n   379→\t\t} else if exitCode == 0 {\n   380→\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   381→\t\t} else {\n   382→\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"container exited with code %d\", exitCode))\n   383→\t\t}\n   384→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   385→\t}\n   386→\n   387→\t// Fire evolution trigger if configured\n   388→\tif s.evolution != nil {\n   389→\t\ts.evolution.Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)\n   390→\t}\n   391→\n   392→\t// Merge is handled as a workflow step in host.cloche, not here.\n   393→\n   394→\t// Container retention policy:\n   395→\t// - Failed runs: always keep the container for debugging\n   396→\t// - Successful runs + --keep-container: keep the container\n   397→\t// - Successful runs without --keep-container: remove the container\n   398→\trunFinal, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   399→\trunFailed := runFinal != nil && (runFinal.State == domain.RunStateFailed || runFinal.State == domain.RunStateCancelled)\n   400→\n   401→\tif keepContainer || runFailed {\n   402→\t\treason := \"--keep-container\"\n   403→\t\tif runFailed {\n   404→\t\t\treason = \"run failed\"\n   405→\t\t}\n   406→\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: keeping container %s (%s)\", runID, containerID, reason)\n   407→\t\tif runFinal != nil {\n   408→\t\t\trunFinal.ContainerKept = true\n   409→\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, runFinal)\n   410→\t\t}\n   411→\t} else {\n   412→\t\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   413→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to remove container %s: %v\", runID, containerID, err)\n   414→\t\t} else {\n   415→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: removed container %s\", runID, containerID)\n   416→\t\t}\n   417→\t}\n   418→\n   419→\t// Cleanup mapping\n   420→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   421→\tdelete(s.runIDs, runID)\n   422→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   423→}\n   424→\n   425→func (s *ClocheServer) ListRuns(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ListRunsRequest) (*pb.ListRunsResponse, error) {\n   426→\tfilter := domain.RunListFilter{\n   427→\t\tProjectDir: req.ProjectDir,\n   428→\t\tState:      domain.RunState(req.State),\n   429→\t\tTaskID:     req.TaskId,\n   430→\t\tLimit:      int(req.Limit),\n   431→\t}\n   432→\n   433→\t// When no project filter and not --all, default to last hour\n   434→\tif filter.ProjectDir == \"\" && !req.All {\n   435→\t\tfilter.Since = time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour)\n   436→\t}\n   437→\n   438→\truns, err := s.store.ListRunsFiltered(ctx, filter)\n   439→\tif err != nil {\n   440→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing runs: %w\", err)\n   441→\t}\n   442→\n   443→\tresp := &pb.ListRunsResponse{}\n   444→\tfor _, run := range runs {\n   445→\t\tresp.Runs = append(resp.Runs, &pb.RunSummary{\n   446→\t\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n   447→\t\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n   448→\t\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n   449→\t\t\tStartedAt:    run.StartedAt.String(),\n   450→\t\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n   451→\t\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n   452→\t\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n   453→\t\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n   454→\t\t\tProjectDir:   run.ProjectDir,\n   455→\t\t})\n   456→\t}\n   457→\treturn resp, nil\n   458→}\n   459→\n   460→func (s *ClocheServer) GetStatus(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetStatusRequest) (*pb.GetStatusResponse, error) {\n   461→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   462→\tif err != nil {\n   463→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"getting run: %w\", err)\n   464→\t}\n   465→\n   466→\tresp := &pb.GetStatusResponse{\n   467→\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n   468→\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n   469→\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n   470→\t\tCurrentStep:  strings.Join(run.ActiveSteps, \",\"),\n   471→\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n   472→\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n   473→\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n   474→\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n   475→\t}\n   476→\n   477→\t// Check container liveness\n   478→\tif run.ContainerID != \"\" && s.container != nil {\n   479→\t\tif cs, err := s.container.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID); err == nil {\n   480→\t\t\tresp.ContainerAlive = cs.Running\n   481→\t\t\tif !cs.Running && !cs.FinishedAt.IsZero() {\n   482→\t\t\t\tresp.ContainerDeadSince = cs.FinishedAt.Format(time.RFC3339Nano)\n   483→\t\t\t}\n   484→\t\t}\n   485→\t}\n   486→\n   487→\t// Load step executions from captures store if available\n   488→\tif s.captures != nil {\n   489→\t\tcaptures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n   490→\t\tif err == nil {\n   491→\t\t\tfor _, exec := range captures {\n   492→\t\t\t\tresp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n   493→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:    exec.StepName,\n   494→\t\t\t\t\tResult:      exec.Result,\n   495→\t\t\t\t\tStartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   496→\t\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   497→\t\t\t\t})\n   498→\t\t\t}\n   499→\t\t}\n   500→\t} else {\n   501→\t\tfor _, exec := range run.StepExecutions {\n   502→\t\t\tresp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n   503→\t\t\t\tStepName:    exec.StepName,\n   504→\t\t\t\tResult:      exec.Result,\n   505→\t\t\t\tStartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   506→\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   507→\t\t\t})\n   508→\t\t}\n   509→\t}\n   510→\n   511→\treturn resp, nil\n   512→}\n   513→\n   514→func (s *ClocheServer) StreamLogs(req *pb.StreamLogsRequest, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   515→\tctx := stream.Context()\n   516→\n   517→\t_ = followFromContext(ctx) // follow is implicit for active runs\n   518→\tlimit := limitFromContext(ctx)\n   519→\n   520→\t// Verify run exists\n   521→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   522→\tif err != nil {\n   523→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found: %w\", req.RunId, err)\n   524→\t}\n   525→\n   526→\t// If step_name or log_type filter is set, serve content directly from the log index\n   527→\tif req.StepName != \"\" || req.LogType != \"\" {\n   528→\t\treturn s.streamFilteredLogs(ctx, req, run, stream, limit)\n   529→\t}\n   530→\n   531→\tisActive := run.State == domain.RunStateRunning || run.State == domain.RunStatePending\n   532→\n   533→\t// Active runs always stream live output (follow mode is implicit).\n   534→\t// The -f flag is accepted but redundant for active runs.\n   535→\tif isActive && s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   536→\t\treturn s.streamFollowLogs(req.RunId, run, stream, limit)\n   537→\t}\n   538→\n   539→\t// Check for full.log first — if it exists, serve it as the unified log\n   540→\tfullLogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n   541→\tif data, readErr := os.ReadFile(fullLogPath); readErr == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   542→\t\tmsg := applyLimit(string(data), limit)\n   543→\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   544→\t\t\tType:    \"full_log\",\n   545→\t\t\tMessage: msg,\n   546→\t\t}); err != nil {\n   547→\t\t\treturn err\n   548→\t\t}\n   549→\t\tif !isActive {\n   550→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   551→\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   552→\t\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   553→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   554→\t\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   555→\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   556→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   557→\t\t\t}\n   558→\t\t}\n   559→\t\treturn nil\n   560→\t}\n   561→\n   562→\tif s.captures == nil {\n   563→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"captures store not configured\")\n   564→\t}\n   565→\n   566→\t// Fall back to capture-based streaming\n   567→\tcaptures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n   568→\tif err != nil {\n   569→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"getting captures: %w\", err)\n   570→\t}\n   571→\n   572→\tfor _, exec := range captures {\n   573→\t\t// Captures are stored as separate rows: one for step_started (no Result)\n   574→\t\t// and one for step_completed (has Result).\n   575→\t\tif exec.Result == \"\" {\n   576→\t\t\tentry := &pb.LogEntry{\n   577→\t\t\t\tType:      \"step_started\",\n   578→\t\t\t\tStepName:  exec.StepName,\n   579→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   580→\t\t\t}\n   581→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(entry); err != nil {\n   582→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   583→\t\t\t}\n   584→\t\t} else {\n   585→\t\t\t// Read step output from per-step output file.\n   586→\t\t\t// Container runs write .log, host runs write .out — try both.\n   587→\t\t\tvar output string\n   588→\t\t\tfor _, ext := range []string{\".log\", \".out\"} {\n   589→\t\t\t\toutputPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\", exec.StepName+ext)\n   590→\t\t\t\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath); err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   591→\t\t\t\t\toutput = string(data)\n   592→\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n   593→\t\t\t\t}\n   594→\t\t\t}\n   595→\t\t\tentry := &pb.LogEntry{\n   596→\t\t\t\tType:      \"step_completed\",\n   597→\t\t\t\tStepName:  exec.StepName,\n   598→\t\t\t\tResult:    exec.Result,\n   599→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   600→\t\t\t\tMessage:   applyLimit(output, limit),\n   601→\t\t\t}\n   602→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(entry); err != nil {\n   603→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   604→\t\t\t}\n   605→\t\t}\n   606→\t}\n   607→\n   608→\t// Send run completion entry\n   609→\tif !isActive {\n   610→\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   611→\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   612→\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   613→\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   614→\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   615→\t\t}); err != nil {\n   616→\t\t\treturn err\n   617→\t\t}\n   618→\t}\n   619→\n   620→\treturn nil\n   621→}\n   622→\n   623→// followFromContext checks for the follow flag in gRPC metadata.\n   624→func followFromContext(ctx context.Context) bool {\n   625→\tmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n   626→\tif !ok {\n   627→\t\treturn false\n   628→\t}\n   629→\tvals := md.Get(\"x-cloche-follow\")\n   630→\treturn len(vals) > 0 && vals[0] == \"true\"\n   631→}\n   632→\n   633→// limitFromContext reads the line limit from gRPC metadata.\n   634→// Returns 0 when no limit is set.\n   635→func limitFromContext(ctx context.Context) int {\n   636→\tmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n   637→\tif !ok {\n   638→\t\treturn 0\n   639→\t}\n   640→\tvals := md.Get(\"x-cloche-limit\")\n   641→\tif len(vals) == 0 {\n   642→\t\treturn 0\n   643→\t}\n   644→\tn, err := strconv.Atoi(vals[0])\n   645→\tif err != nil || n <= 0 {\n   646→\t\treturn 0\n   647→\t}\n   648→\treturn n\n   649→}\n   650→\n   651→// applyLimit returns the last n lines of content. If n <= 0, returns content unchanged.\n   652→func applyLimit(content string, n int) string {\n   653→\tif n <= 0 {\n   654→\t\treturn content\n   655→\t}\n   656→\tlines := strings.Split(content, \"\\n\")\n   657→\t// Remove trailing empty line from final newline\n   658→\tif len(lines) > 0 && lines[len(lines)-1] == \"\" {\n   659→\t\tlines = lines[:len(lines)-1]\n   660→\t}\n   661→\tif len(lines) <= n {\n   662→\t\treturn content\n   663→\t}\n   664→\treturn strings.Join(lines[len(lines)-n:], \"\\n\") + \"\\n\"\n   665→}\n   666→\n   667→// streamFollowLogs sends existing log content then tails live output from the\n   668→// broadcaster. It combines snapshot + live streaming (like tail -f).\n   669→func (s *ClocheServer) streamFollowLogs(runID string, run *domain.Run, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry], limit int) error {\n   670→\t// Subscribe first so we don't miss lines written between read and subscribe.\n   671→\tsub := s.logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)\n   672→\tdefer s.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(runID, sub)\n   673→\n   674→\t// Send existing full.log content if available.\n   675→\tfullLogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n   676→\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(fullLogPath); err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   677→\t\tmsg := applyLimit(string(data), limit)\n   678→\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   679→\t\t\tType:    \"full_log\",\n   680→\t\t\tMessage: msg,\n   681→\t\t}); err != nil {\n   682→\t\t\treturn err\n   683→\t\t}\n   684→\t}\n   685→\n   686→\t// Now tail live output from the broadcaster.\n   687→\tctx := stream.Context()\n   688→\tfor {\n   689→\t\tselect {\n   690→\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n   691→\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\n   692→\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n   693→\t\t\tif !ok {\n   694→\t\t\t\t// Run completed — send terminal entry.\n   695→\t\t\t\tr, err := s.store.GetRun(context.Background(), runID)\n   696→\t\t\t\tif err == nil && r.State != domain.RunStateRunning && r.State != domain.RunStatePending {\n   697→\t\t\t\t\t_ = stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   698→\t\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   699→\t\t\t\t\t\tResult:    string(r.State),\n   700→\t\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: r.CompletedAt.String(),\n   701→\t\t\t\t\t\tMessage:   r.ErrorMessage,\n   702→\t\t\t\t\t})\n   703→\t\t\t\t}\n   704→\t\t\t\treturn nil\n   705→\t\t\t}\n   706→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   707→\t\t\t\tType:      \"log\",\n   708→\t\t\t\tStepName:  line.StepName,\n   709→\t\t\t\tMessage:   line.Content,\n   710→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: line.Timestamp,\n   711→\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   712→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   713→\t\t\t}\n   714→\t\t}\n   715→\t}\n   716→}\n   717→\n   718→// streamFilteredLogs serves log content filtered by step name and/or log type.\n   719→// It uses the log index when available, falling back to file path conventions.\n   720→func (s *ClocheServer) streamFilteredLogs(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StreamLogsRequest, run *domain.Run, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry], limit int) error {\n   721→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\")\n   722→\n   723→\t// Try log index first\n   724→\tif s.logStore != nil {\n   725→\t\tvar logFiles []*ports.LogFileEntry\n   726→\t\tvar err error\n   727→\n   728→\t\tif req.StepName != \"\" && req.LogType != \"\" {\n   729→\t\t\t// Filter by both step and type\n   730→\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, req.RunId, req.StepName)\n   731→\t\t\tif err == nil {\n   732→\t\t\t\tfiltered := logFiles[:0]\n   733→\t\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n   734→\t\t\t\t\tif lf.FileType == req.LogType {\n   735→\t\t\t\t\t\tfiltered = append(filtered, lf)\n   736→\t\t\t\t\t}\n   737→\t\t\t\t}\n   738→\t\t\t\tlogFiles = filtered\n   739→\t\t\t}\n   740→\t\t} else if req.StepName != \"\" {\n   741→\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, req.RunId, req.StepName)\n   742→\t\t} else {\n   743→\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFileByType(ctx, req.RunId, req.LogType)\n   744→\t\t}\n   745→\n   746→\t\tif err == nil && len(logFiles) > 0 {\n   747→\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n   748→\t\t\t\tdata, readErr := os.ReadFile(lf.FilePath)\n   749→\t\t\t\tif readErr != nil {\n   750→\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   751→\t\t\t\t}\n   752→\t\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   753→\t\t\t\t\tType:     lf.FileType + \"_log\",\n   754→\t\t\t\t\tStepName: lf.StepName,\n   755→\t\t\t\t\tMessage:  applyLimit(string(data), limit),\n   756→\t\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   757→\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n   758→\t\t\t\t}\n   759→\t\t\t}\n   760→\t\t\treturn nil\n   761→\t\t}\n   762→\t}\n   763→\n   764→\t// Fall back to file path conventions\n   765→\tif req.StepName != \"\" {\n   766→\t\tvar logPath string\n   767→\t\tswitch req.LogType {\n   768→\t\tcase \"llm\":\n   769→\t\t\tlogPath = filepath.Join(outputDir, \"llm-\"+req.StepName+\".log\")\n   770→\t\tdefault:\n   771→\t\t\tlogPath = filepath.Join(outputDir, req.StepName+\".log\")\n   772→\t\t}\n   773→\n   774→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(logPath)\n   775→\t\tif err != nil {\n   776→\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"log file not found for step %q: %w\", req.StepName, err)\n   777→\t\t}\n   778→\t\treturn stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   779→\t\t\tType:     \"step_log\",\n   780→\t\t\tStepName: req.StepName,\n   781→\t\t\tMessage:  applyLimit(string(data), limit),\n   782→\t\t})\n   783→\t}\n   784→\n   785→\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"no log files found matching filter\")\n   786→}\n   787→\n   788→// streamLiveLogs subscribes to the broadcaster and streams log lines in real\n   789→// time for an active run. The stream closes when the run completes or the\n   790→// client disconnects.\n   791→func (s *ClocheServer) streamLiveLogs(runID string, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   792→\tsub := s.logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)\n   793→\tdefer s.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(runID, sub)\n   794→\n   795→\tctx := stream.Context()\n   796→\tfor {\n   797→\t\tselect {\n   798→\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n   799→\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\n   800→\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n   801→\t\t\tif !ok {\n   802→\t\t\t\t// Run completed — send terminal entry.\n   803→\t\t\t\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(context.Background(), runID)\n   804→\t\t\t\tif err == nil && run.State != domain.RunStateRunning && run.State != domain.RunStatePending {\n   805→\t\t\t\t\t_ = stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   806→\t\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   807→\t\t\t\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   808→\t\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   809→\t\t\t\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   810→\t\t\t\t\t})\n   811→\t\t\t\t}\n   812→\t\t\t\treturn nil\n   813→\t\t\t}\n   814→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   815→\t\t\t\tType:      \"log\",\n   816→\t\t\t\tStepName:  line.StepName,\n   817→\t\t\t\tMessage:   line.Content,\n   818→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: line.Timestamp,\n   819→\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   820→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   821→\t\t\t}\n   822→\t\t}\n   823→\t}\n   824→}\n   825→\n   826→func (s *ClocheServer) StopRun(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StopRunRequest) (*pb.StopRunResponse, error) {\n   827→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   828→\tcontainerID, ok := s.runIDs[req.RunId]\n   829→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   830→\n   831→\tif !ok {\n   832→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found or already completed\", req.RunId)\n   833→\t}\n   834→\n   835→\tif err := s.container.Stop(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   836→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"stopping run: %w\", err)\n   837→\t}\n   838→\n   839→\t// Mark as cancelled in store\n   840→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   841→\tif err == nil {\n   842→\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateCancelled)\n   843→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   844→\t}\n   845→\n   846→\treturn &pb.StopRunResponse{}, nil\n   847→}\n   848→\n   849→func (s *ClocheServer) DeleteContainer(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DeleteContainerRequest) (*pb.DeleteContainerResponse, error) {\n   850→\tif s.container == nil {\n   851→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n   852→\t}\n   853→\n   854→\tid := req.Id\n   855→\tif id == \"\" {\n   856→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"id is required\")\n   857→\t}\n   858→\n   859→\t// Try to resolve as a run ID first\n   860→\tcontainerID := id\n   861→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, id)\n   862→\tif err == nil {\n   863→\t\t// It's a run ID — use the container ID from the run record\n   864→\t\tif run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   865→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q has no associated container\", id)\n   866→\t\t}\n   867→\t\tcontainerID = run.ContainerID\n   868→\t}\n   869→\n   870→\t// Remove the container\n   871→\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   872→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"removing container: %w\", err)\n   873→\t}\n   874→\n   875→\t// If we resolved a run, clear the container_kept flag\n   876→\tif run != nil {\n   877→\t\trun.ContainerKept = false\n   878→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   879→\t}\n   880→\n   881→\treturn &pb.DeleteContainerResponse{}, nil\n   882→}\n   883→\n   884→func (s *ClocheServer) EnableLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.EnableLoopRequest) (*pb.EnableLoopResponse, error) {\n   885→\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n   886→\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n   887→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n   888→\t}\n   889→\n   890→\t// Verify at least one host workflow exists in the project.\n   891→\thostWorkflows, err := host.FindHostWorkflows(projectDir)\n   892→\tif err != nil || len(hostWorkflows) == 0 {\n   893→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no host workflows found in %s/.cloche/\", projectDir)\n   894→\t}\n   895→\n   896→\t// Load project config for defaults.\n   897→\tprojCfg, _ := config.Load(projectDir)\n   898→\n   899→\tmaxConc := int(req.MaxConcurrent)\n   900→\tif maxConc <= 0 {\n   901→\t\tmaxConc = projCfg.Orchestration.Concurrency\n   902→\t}\n   903→\tif maxConc <= 0 {\n   904→\t\tmaxConc = 1\n   905→\t}\n   906→\n   907→\tstagger := time.Duration(float64(time.Second) * projCfg.Orchestration.StaggerSeconds)\n   908→\n   909→\t// Compute dedup timeout from config (default 5 minutes).\n   910→\tdedupTimeout := time.Duration(float64(time.Second) * projCfg.Orchestration.DedupSeconds)\n   911→\n   912→\tloopCfg := host.LoopConfig{\n   913→\t\tProjectDir:    projectDir,\n   914→\t\tMaxConcurrent: maxConc,\n   915→\t\tStaggerDelay:  stagger,\n   916→\t\tDedupTimeout:  dedupTimeout,\n   917→\t\tStopOnError:   projCfg.Orchestration.StopOnError,\n   918→\t}\n   919→\n   920→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   921→\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n   922→\n   923→\t// Stop existing loop if running.\n   924→\tif existing, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n   925→\t\texisting.Stop()\n   926→\t}\n   927→\n   928→\t// Check if project defines a list-tasks workflow for three-phase mode.\n   929→\tvar loop *host.Loop\n   930→\tif _, hasListTasks := hostWorkflows[\"list-tasks\"]; hasListTasks {\n   931→\t\tloop = s.createPhaseLoop(loopCfg, projectDir, dedupTimeout)\n   932→\t} else {\n   933→\t\tloop = s.createLegacyLoop(loopCfg, projectDir, projCfg, dedupTimeout)\n   934→\t}\n   935→\n   936→\ts.loops[projectDir] = loop\n   937→\tloop.Start()\n   938→\n   939→\treturn &pb.EnableLoopResponse{}, nil\n   940→}\n   941→\n   942→// createPhaseLoop creates a three-phase orchestration loop using list-tasks,\n   943→// main, and finalize host workflows from any .cloche file.\n   944→func (s *ClocheServer) createPhaseLoop(loopCfg host.LoopConfig, projectDir string, dedupTimeout time.Duration) *host.Loop {\n   945→\t// Phase 1: list-tasks function\n   946→\tlistTasksFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string) ([]host.Task, error) {\n   947→\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   948→\t\t\tDispatcher: s,\n   949→\t\t\tStore:      s.store,\n   950→\t\t}\n   951→\t\ttasks, _, err := host.RunListTasksWorkflow(ctx, runner, projDir)\n   952→\t\treturn tasks, err\n   953→\t}\n   954→\n   955→\t// Phase 2: main function\n   956→\tmainFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n   957→\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   958→\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   959→\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   960→\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   961→\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   962→\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n   963→\t\t}\n   964→\t\treturn runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"main\")\n   965→\t}\n   966→\n   967→\t// Phase 3: finalize function (optional — only if a finalize host workflow exists)\n   968→\tvar finalizeFn host.FinalizeFunc\n   969→\tif hostWFs, err := host.FindHostWorkflows(projectDir); err == nil {\n   970→\t\tif _, hasFinalize := hostWFs[\"finalize\"]; hasFinalize {\n   971→\t\t\tfinalizeFn = func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string, mainResult *host.RunResult) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n   972→\t\t\t\tmainRunID := \"\"\n   973→\t\t\t\tmainOutcome := \"failed\"\n   974→\t\t\t\tif mainResult != nil {\n   975→\t\t\t\t\tmainRunID = mainResult.RunID\n   976→\t\t\t\t\tmainOutcome = string(mainResult.State)\n   977→\t\t\t\t}\n   978→\t\t\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   979→\t\t\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   980→\t\t\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   981→\t\t\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   982→\t\t\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   983→\t\t\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n   984→\t\t\t\t\tExtraEnv: []string{\n   985→\t\t\t\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID=\" + mainRunID,\n   986→\t\t\t\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME=\" + mainOutcome,\n   987→\t\t\t\t\t},\n   988→\t\t\t\t}\n   989→\t\t\t\treturn runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"finalize\")\n   990→\t\t\t}\n   991→\t\t}\n   992→\t}\n   993→\n   994→\tlog.Printf(\"orchestration loop: three-phase mode enabled for %s (list-tasks + main + finalize, dedup=%s)\", projectDir, dedupTimeout)\n   995→\treturn host.NewPhaseLoop(loopCfg, s.store, listTasksFn, mainFn, finalizeFn)\n   996→}\n   997→\n   998→// createLegacyLoop creates a legacy single-function orchestration loop.\n   999→func (s *ClocheServer) createLegacyLoop(loopCfg host.LoopConfig, projectDir string, projCfg *config.Config, dedupTimeout time.Duration) *host.Loop {\n  1000→\trunFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n  1001→\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n  1002→\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n  1003→\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n  1004→\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n  1005→\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n  1006→\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n  1007→\t\t}\n  1008→\t\treturn runner.Run(ctx, projDir)\n  1009→\t}\n  1010→\n  1011→\tloop := host.NewLoop(loopCfg, s.store, runFn)\n  1012→\n  1013→\t// Configure daemon-managed task assignment if a list-tasks command is set.\n  1014→\tif cmd := projCfg.Orchestration.ListTasksCommand; cmd != \"\" {\n  1015→\t\tloop.SetTaskAssigner(&host.ScriptTaskAssigner{Command: cmd})\n  1016→\t\tlog.Printf(\"orchestration loop: task assignment enabled for %s (command=%q, dedup=%s)\", projectDir, cmd, dedupTimeout)\n  1017→\t}\n  1018→\n  1019→\treturn loop\n  1020→}\n  1021→\n  1022→// GetLoopTasks returns the current task pipeline state for a project's\n  1023→// orchestration loop, formatted as web.TaskEntry values. Returns nil if no\n  1024→// loop is active for the project.\n  1025→func (s *ClocheServer) GetLoopTasks(projectDir string) []web.TaskEntry {\n  1026→\ts.mu.Lock()\n  1027→\tloop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]\n  1028→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n  1029→\tif !ok {\n  1030→\t\treturn nil\n  1031→\t}\n  1032→\tsnapshot := loop.GetTaskSnapshot()\n  1033→\n  1034→\t// Build a set of task IDs that have active (pending/running) runs.\n  1035→\tactiveTaskIDs := make(map[string]bool)\n  1036→\tctx := context.Background()\n  1037→\tallRuns, _ := s.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, time.Time{})\n  1038→\tfor _, r := range allRuns {\n  1039→\t\tif r.TaskID != \"\" && (r.State == domain.RunStatePending || r.State == domain.RunStateRunning) {\n  1040→\t\t\tactiveTaskIDs[r.TaskID] = true\n  1041→\t\t}\n  1042→\t}\n  1043→\n  1044→\tentries := make([]web.TaskEntry, len(snapshot))\n  1045→\tfor i, e := range snapshot {\n  1046→\t\tentry := web.TaskEntry{\n  1047→\t\t\tID:          e.Task.ID,\n  1048→\t\t\tStatus:      e.Task.Status,\n  1049→\t\t\tTitle:       e.Task.Title,\n  1050→\t\t\tDescription: e.Task.Description,\n  1051→\t\t\tMetadata:    e.Task.Metadata,\n  1052→\t\t\tAssigned:    e.Assigned,\n  1053→\t\t\tRunID:       e.RunID,\n  1054→\t\t}\n  1055→\t\tif !e.AssignedAt.IsZero() {\n  1056→\t\t\tentry.AssignedAt = e.AssignedAt.Format(time.RFC3339)\n  1057→\t\t}\n  1058→\t\t// Stale: task is in_progress but has no active worker.\n  1059→\t\tif host.TaskStatus(e.Task.Status) == host.TaskStatusInProgress && !activeTaskIDs[e.Task.ID] {\n  1060→\t\t\tentry.Stale = true\n  1061→\t\t}\n  1062→\t\tentries[i] = entry\n  1063→\t}\n  1064→\treturn entries\n  1065→}\n  1066→\n  1067→// ReleaseTask runs the release-task host workflow for a specific task,\n  1068→// returning it to open status.\n  1069→func (s *ClocheServer) ReleaseTask(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, taskID string) error {\n  1070→\trunner := &host.Runner{\n  1071→\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n  1072→\t\tStore:        s.store,\n  1073→\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n  1074→\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n  1075→\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n  1076→\t}\n  1077→\tresult, err := runner.RunNamed(ctx, projectDir, \"release-task\")\n  1078→\tif err != nil {\n  1079→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"release-task workflow failed: %w\", err)\n  1080→\t}\n  1081→\tif result.State != domain.RunStateSucceeded {\n  1082→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"release-task workflow finished with state %s\", result.State)\n  1083→\t}\n  1084→\treturn nil\n  1085→}\n  1086→\n  1087→func (s *ClocheServer) DisableLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DisableLoopRequest) (*pb.DisableLoopResponse, error) {\n  1088→\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n  1089→\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n  1090→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n  1091→\t}\n  1092→\n  1093→\ts.mu.Lock()\n  1094→\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n  1095→\n  1096→\tif loop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n  1097→\t\tloop.Stop()\n  1098→\t\tdelete(s.loops, projectDir)\n  1099→\t}\n  1100→\n  1101→\treturn &pb.DisableLoopResponse{}, nil\n  1102→}\n  1103→\n  1104→func (s *ClocheServer) ResumeLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ResumeLoopRequest) (*pb.ResumeLoopResponse, error) {\n  1105→\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n  1106→\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n  1107→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n  1108→\t}\n  1109→\n  1110→\ts.mu.Lock()\n  1111→\tloop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]\n  1112→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n  1113→\n  1114→\tif !ok || loop == nil {\n  1115→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no orchestration loop for %s\", projectDir)\n  1116→\t}\n  1117→\n  1118→\tloop.Resume()\n  1119→\treturn &pb.ResumeLoopResponse{}, nil\n  1120→}\n  1121→\n  1122→func (s *ClocheServer) GetProjectInfo(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetProjectInfoRequest) (*pb.GetProjectInfoResponse, error) {\n  1123→\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n  1124→\n  1125→\t// Resolve by name if provided.\n  1126→\tif req.Name != \"\" && projectDir == \"\" {\n  1127→\t\tprojects, err := s.store.ListProjects(ctx)\n  1128→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1129→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing projects: %w\", err)\n  1130→\t\t}\n  1131→\t\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n  1132→\t\tfound := false\n  1133→\t\tfor dir, label := range labels {\n  1134→\t\t\tif label == req.Name {\n  1135→\t\t\t\tprojectDir = dir\n  1136→\t\t\t\tfound = true\n  1137→\t\t\t\tbreak\n  1138→\t\t\t}\n  1139→\t\t}\n  1140→\t\tif !found {\n  1141→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project %q not found\", req.Name)\n  1142→\t\t}\n  1143→\t}\n  1144→\n  1145→\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n  1146→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir or name is required\")\n  1147→\t}\n  1148→\n  1149→\t// Derive project label.\n  1150→\tprojects, _ := s.store.ListProjects(ctx)\n  1151→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n  1152→\tlabel := labels[projectDir]\n  1153→\tif label == \"\" {\n  1154→\t\tlabel = filepath.Base(projectDir)\n  1155→\t}\n  1156→\n  1157→\t// Load config.\n  1158→\tcfg, _ := config.Load(projectDir)\n  1159→\n  1160→\t// Check loop state.\n  1161→\ts.mu.Lock()\n  1162→\tloop, loopExists := s.loops[projectDir]\n  1163→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n  1164→\tloopRunning := loopExists && loop != nil && loop.Running()\n  1165→\n  1166→\t// Get active runs.\n  1167→\tallRuns, _ := s.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, time.Time{})\n  1168→\tvar activeRuns []*pb.RunSummary\n  1169→\tfor _, run := range allRuns {\n  1170→\t\tif run.State == domain.RunStatePending || run.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n  1171→\t\t\tactiveRuns = append(activeRuns, &pb.RunSummary{\n  1172→\t\t\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n  1173→\t\t\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n  1174→\t\t\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n  1175→\t\t\t\tStartedAt:    run.StartedAt.String(),\n  1176→\t\t\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n  1177→\t\t\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n  1178→\t\t\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n  1179→\t\t\t})\n  1180→\t\t}\n  1181→\t}\n  1182→\n  1183→\t// Discover workflows.\n  1184→\tvar containerWorkflows, hostWorkflows []string\n  1185→\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\")\n  1186→\tentries, _ := filepath.Glob(filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"*.cloche\"))\n  1187→\tfor _, path := range entries {\n  1188→\t\tbase := filepath.Base(path)\n  1189→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n  1190→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1191→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1192→\t\t}\n  1193→\t\tif base == \"host.cloche\" {\n  1194→\t\t\twfs, err := dsl.ParseAllForHost(string(data))\n  1195→\t\t\tif err != nil {\n  1196→\t\t\t\tcontinue\n  1197→\t\t\t}\n  1198→\t\t\tfor name := range wfs {\n  1199→\t\t\t\thostWorkflows = append(hostWorkflows, name)\n  1200→\t\t\t}\n  1201→\t\t} else {\n  1202→\t\t\twf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n  1203→\t\t\tif err != nil {\n  1204→\t\t\t\tcontinue\n  1205→\t\t\t}\n  1206→\t\t\tcontainerWorkflows = append(containerWorkflows, wf.Name)\n  1207→\t\t}\n  1208→\t}\n  1209→\n  1210→\tsort.Strings(containerWorkflows)\n  1211→\tsort.Strings(hostWorkflows)\n  1212→\n  1213→\t// Check if loop is halted due to an error.\n  1214→\tvar errorHalted bool\n  1215→\tvar haltError string\n  1216→\tif loopExists && loop != nil {\n  1217→\t\terrorHalted, haltError = loop.Halted()\n  1218→\t}\n  1219→\n  1220→\treturn &pb.GetProjectInfoResponse{\n  1221→\t\tProjectDir:         projectDir,\n  1222→\t\tName:               label,\n  1223→\t\tActive:             cfg.Active,\n  1224→\t\tConcurrency:        int32(cfg.Orchestration.Concurrency),\n  1225→\t\tStaggerSeconds:     cfg.Orchestration.StaggerSeconds,\n  1226→\t\tDedupSeconds:       cfg.Orchestration.DedupSeconds,\n  1227→\t\tEvolutionEnabled:   cfg.Evolution.Enabled,\n  1228→\t\tLoopRunning:        loopRunning,\n  1229→\t\tActiveRuns:         activeRuns,\n  1230→\t\tContainerWorkflows: containerWorkflows,\n  1231→\t\tHostWorkflows:      hostWorkflows,\n  1232→\t\tStopOnError:        cfg.Orchestration.StopOnError,\n  1233→\t\tErrorHalted:        errorHalted,\n  1234→\t\tHaltError:          haltError,\n  1235→\t}, nil\n  1236→}\n  1237→\n  1238→// projectLabels maps each project directory to a short display label.\n  1239→// Uses basename unless there are conflicts, in which case parent/basename is used.\n  1240→func projectLabels(dirs []string) map[string]string {\n  1241→\tlabels := make(map[string]string, len(dirs))\n  1242→\tbyBase := map[string][]string{}\n  1243→\tfor _, d := range dirs {\n  1244→\t\tbase := filepath.Base(d)\n  1245→\t\tbyBase[base] = append(byBase[base], d)\n  1246→\t}\n  1247→\tfor base, paths := range byBase {\n  1248→\t\tif len(paths) == 1 {\n  1249→\t\t\tlabels[paths[0]] = base\n  1250→\t\t} else {\n  1251→\t\t\tfor _, p := range paths {\n  1252→\t\t\t\tparent := filepath.Base(filepath.Dir(p))\n  1253→\t\t\t\tlabels[p] = parent + \"/\" + base\n  1254→\t\t\t}\n  1255→\t\t}\n  1256→\t}\n  1257→\treturn labels\n  1258→}\n  1259→\n  1260→func (s *ClocheServer) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetVersionRequest) (*pb.GetVersionResponse, error) {\n  1261→\treturn &pb.GetVersionResponse{Version: version.Version()}, nil\n  1262→}\n  1263→\n  1264→func (s *ClocheServer) Shutdown(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ShutdownRequest) (*pb.ShutdownResponse, error) {\n  1265→\tif !req.Force {\n  1266→\t\t// Check for active container runs.\n  1267→\t\ts.mu.Lock()\n  1268→\t\tactiveRuns := len(s.runIDs)\n  1269→\t\ts.mu.Unlock()\n  1270→\t\tif activeRuns > 0 {\n  1271→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"cannot shutdown: %d run(s) still active (use --force to override)\", activeRuns)\n  1272→\t\t}\n  1273→\t}\n  1274→\n  1275→\t// Stop all orchestration loops.\n  1276→\ts.mu.Lock()\n  1277→\tfor _, loop := range s.loops {\n  1278→\t\tloop.Stop()\n  1279→\t}\n  1280→\ts.loops = make(map[string]*host.Loop)\n  1281→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n  1282→\n  1283→\tif s.shutdownFn == nil {\n  1284→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"shutdown not configured\")\n  1285→\t}\n  1286→\tgo s.shutdownFn()\n  1287→\treturn &pb.ShutdownResponse{}, nil\n  1288→}\n  1289→\n  1290→// indexLogFiles scans the extracted output directory and creates log_files index entries.\n  1291→func (s *ClocheServer) indexLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID, outputDir string) {\n  1292→\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(outputDir)\n  1293→\tif err != nil {\n  1294→\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to read output dir for indexing: %v\", runID, err)\n  1295→\t\treturn\n  1296→\t}\n  1297→\n  1298→\tnow := time.Now()\n  1299→\tfor _, entry := range entries {\n  1300→\t\tif entry.IsDir() {\n  1301→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1302→\t\t}\n  1303→\t\tname := entry.Name()\n  1304→\t\tif !strings.HasSuffix(name, \".log\") {\n  1305→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1306→\t\t}\n  1307→\n  1308→\t\tvar fileType, stepName string\n  1309→\t\tbase := strings.TrimSuffix(name, \".log\")\n  1310→\n  1311→\t\tswitch {\n  1312→\t\tcase name == \"full.log\":\n  1313→\t\t\tfileType = \"full\"\n  1314→\t\tcase name == \"container.log\":\n  1315→\t\t\t// container.log is internal, not indexed as a user-facing log type\n  1316→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1317→\t\tcase strings.HasPrefix(name, \"llm-\"):\n  1318→\t\t\tfileType = \"llm\"\n  1319→\t\t\tstepName = strings.TrimPrefix(base, \"llm-\")\n  1320→\t\tdefault:\n  1321→\t\t\tfileType = \"script\"\n  1322→\t\t\tstepName = base\n  1323→\t\t}\n  1324→\n  1325→\t\tinfo, _ := entry.Info()\n  1326→\t\tvar fileSize int64\n  1327→\t\tif info != nil {\n  1328→\t\t\tfileSize = info.Size()\n  1329→\t\t}\n  1330→\n  1331→\t\tlogEntry := &ports.LogFileEntry{\n  1332→\t\t\tRunID:     runID,\n  1333→\t\t\tStepName:  stepName,\n  1334→\t\t\tFileType:  fileType,\n  1335→\t\t\tFilePath:  filepath.Join(outputDir, name),\n  1336→\t\t\tFileSize:  fileSize,\n  1337→\t\t\tCreatedAt: now,\n  1338→\t\t}\n  1339→\t\tif err := s.logStore.SaveLogFile(ctx, logEntry); err != nil {\n  1340→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to index log file %s: %v\", runID, name, err)\n  1341→\t\t}\n  1342→\t}\n  1343→}\n  1344→\n  1345→func gitHEAD(dir string) string {\n  1346→\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\")\n  1347→\tcmd.Dir = dir\n  1348→\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n  1349→\tif err != nil {\n  1350→\t\treturn \"\"\n  1351→\t}\n  1352→\treturn strings.TrimSpace(string(out))\n  1353→}\n  1354→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f29cf043-1251-4213-84f2-becb34ef1768","uuid":"f5bf39c1-8634-4264-9cf4-7ab824698148","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go","content":"package grpc\n\nimport (\n\t\"bufio\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"log\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"os/exec\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"sort\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tpb \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/docker\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/web\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/config\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/evolution\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/host\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/version\"\n\trpcgrpc \"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n\t\"google.golang.org/grpc/metadata\"\n)\n\ntype ClocheServer struct {\n\tpb.UnimplementedClocheServiceServer\n\tstore        ports.RunStore\n\tcaptures     ports.CaptureStore\n\tlogStore     ports.LogStore\n\tcontainer    ports.ContainerRuntime\n\tdefaultImage string\n\tevolution    *evolution.Trigger\n\tlogBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n\tshutdownFn   func()\n\tmu           sync.Mutex\n\trunIDs       map[string]string      // run_id -> container_id\n\tloops        map[string]*host.Loop  // project_dir -> orchestration loop\n}\n\nfunc NewClocheServer(store ports.RunStore, container ports.ContainerRuntime) *ClocheServer {\n\treturn &ClocheServer{\n\t\tstore:     store,\n\t\tcontainer: container,\n\t\trunIDs:    make(map[string]string),\n\t\tloops:     make(map[string]*host.Loop),\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc NewClocheServerWithCaptures(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, container ports.ContainerRuntime, defaultImage string) *ClocheServer {\n\treturn &ClocheServer{\n\t\tstore:        store,\n\t\tcaptures:     captures,\n\t\tcontainer:    container,\n\t\tdefaultImage: defaultImage,\n\t\trunIDs:       make(map[string]string),\n\t\tloops:        make(map[string]*host.Loop),\n\t}\n}\n\n// SetLogStore attaches a log store to the server for indexing extracted log files.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) SetLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) {\n\ts.logStore = ls\n}\n\n\n// SetEvolution attaches an evolution trigger to the server.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) SetEvolution(trigger *evolution.Trigger) {\n\ts.evolution = trigger\n}\n\n// SetLogBroadcaster attaches a log broadcaster for live-streaming LLM output.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) SetLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) {\n\ts.logBroadcast = b\n}\n\n// SetShutdownFunc sets the callback invoked when the Shutdown RPC is called.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) SetShutdownFunc(fn func()) {\n\ts.shutdownFn = fn\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n\t// Check if this is a host workflow (has host {} block).\n\tif hostWFs, err := host.FindHostWorkflows(req.ProjectDir); err == nil {\n\t\tif _, isHost := hostWFs[req.WorkflowName]; isHost {\n\t\t\treturn s.runHostWorkflow(ctx, req)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tif s.container == nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n\t}\n\n\t// Generate a unique run ID, retrying on collision\n\tvar runID string\n\tfor attempts := 0; attempts < 10; attempts++ {\n\t\trunID = domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n\t\texisting, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tbreak // ID is free\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Reuse if completed more than 1 hour ago\n\t\tif !existing.CompletedAt.IsZero() && time.Since(existing.CompletedAt) > time.Hour {\n\t\t\t_ = s.store.DeleteRun(ctx, runID)\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Write prompt to .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt (run-specific to avoid conflicts)\n\tif req.Prompt != \"\" {\n\t\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(req.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID)\n\t\tif err := os.MkdirAll(clocheDir, 0755); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating .cloche dir: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"prompt.txt\"), []byte(req.Prompt), 0644); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"writing prompt: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\trun := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\n\trun.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\n\trun.Title = req.Title\n\tif err := s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating run: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Resolve image: request-level override, then server default\n\timage := req.Image\n\tif image == \"\" {\n\t\timage = s.defaultImage\n\t}\n\n\t// Launch container start + tracking in background so the RPC returns immediately.\n\t// The run stays in \"pending\" state until the container is up.\n\tgo s.launchAndTrack(runID, image, req.KeepContainer, req)\n\n\treturn &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n}\n\n// runHostWorkflow dispatches a host workflow via the host runner, returning\n// immediately while the workflow runs in a background goroutine.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) runHostWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n\trunID := domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n\n\trunner := &host.Runner{\n\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n\t\tStore:        s.store,\n\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n\t}\n\n\tgo func() {\n\t\trunner.RunNamedWithID(context.Background(), req.ProjectDir, req.WorkflowName, runID)\n\t}()\n\n\treturn &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n}\n\n// launchAndTrack starts the container and then tracks it to completion.\n// It runs in a background goroutine with its own context, independent of the\n// RPC context which may be cancelled after RunWorkflow returns.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) launchAndTrack(runID, image string, keepContainer bool, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) {\n\tctx := context.Background()\n\n\t// Auto-rebuild image if the project Dockerfile has changed since last build.\n\tif ensurer, ok := s.container.(ports.ImageEnsurer); ok {\n\t\tif err := ensurer.EnsureImage(ctx, req.ProjectDir, image); err != nil {\n\t\t\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n\t\t\tif run != nil {\n\t\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to ensure image: %v\", err))\n\t\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to ensure image: %v\", runID, err)\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tbaseSHA := gitHEAD(req.ProjectDir)\n\n\tcontainerID, err := s.container.Start(ctx, ports.ContainerConfig{\n\t\tImage:        image,\n\t\tWorkflowName: req.WorkflowName,\n\t\tProjectDir:   req.ProjectDir,\n\t\tRunID:        runID,\n\t\tNetworkAllow: []string{\"*\"},\n\t})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n\t\tif run != nil {\n\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to start container: %v\", err))\n\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n\t\t}\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to start container: %v\", runID, err)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\ts.runIDs[runID] = containerID\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\n\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n\tif run != nil {\n\t\trun.Start()\n\t\trun.ContainerID = containerID\n\t\trun.BaseSHA = baseSHA\n\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n\t}\n\n\ts.trackRun(runID, containerID, req.ProjectDir, req.WorkflowName, keepContainer)\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) trackRun(runID, containerID, projectDir, workflowName string, keepContainer bool) {\n\tctx := context.Background()\n\n\t// Attach to agent output\n\treader, err := s.container.AttachOutput(ctx, containerID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"failed to attach to output for run %s: %v\", runID, err)\n\t\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Parse JSON-lines status messages\n\tvar reportedResult string // captured from MsgRunCompleted, persisted after branch extraction\n\tvar reportedError string  // captured from MsgError, used to set ErrorMessage on failed runs\n\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(reader)\n\tscanner.Buffer(make([]byte, 0, 256*1024), 1024*1024) // 1MB max to handle large log messages\n\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n\t\tvar msg protocol.StatusMessage\n\t\tif err := json.Unmarshal(scanner.Bytes(), &msg); err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\t// Fast path: log messages don't need store interaction.\n\t\tif msg.Type == protocol.MsgLog {\n\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"llm\",\n\t\t\t\t\tContent:   msg.Message,\n\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tswitch msg.Type {\n\t\tcase protocol.MsgStepStarted:\n\t\t\trun.RecordStepStart(msg.StepName)\n\t\t\tif s.captures != nil {\n\t\t\t\t_ = s.captures.SaveCapture(ctx, runID, &domain.StepExecution{\n\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n\t\t\t\t\tStartedAt: msg.Timestamp,\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"status\",\n\t\t\t\t\tContent:   \"step_started: \" + msg.StepName,\n\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase protocol.MsgStepCompleted:\n\t\t\trun.RecordStepComplete(msg.StepName, msg.Result)\n\t\t\tif s.captures != nil {\n\t\t\t\t_ = s.captures.SaveCapture(ctx, runID, &domain.StepExecution{\n\t\t\t\t\tStepName:    msg.StepName,\n\t\t\t\t\tResult:      msg.Result,\n\t\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: msg.Timestamp,\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"status\",\n\t\t\t\t\tContent:   \"step_completed: \" + msg.StepName + \" -> \" + msg.Result,\n\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase protocol.MsgRunTitle:\n\t\t\tif run.Title == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\trun.Title = msg.Message\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase protocol.MsgError:\n\t\t\treportedError = msg.Message\n\t\t\tcontinue // Don't persist; used during finalization\n\t\tcase protocol.MsgRunCompleted:\n\t\t\treportedResult = msg.Result\n\t\t\tcontinue // Don't persist terminal state yet; branch extraction must finish first\n\t\t}\n\n\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n\t}\n\treader.Close()\n\n\t// Signal live-stream subscribers that this run is done.\n\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n\t\ts.logBroadcast.Finish(runID)\n\t}\n\n\t// Wait for process exit\n\texitCode, err := s.container.Wait(ctx, containerID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"error waiting for run %s: %v\", runID, err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Extract step output files from container before it's removed\n\toutputDst := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"output\")\n\tif err := os.MkdirAll(outputDst, 0755); err == nil {\n\t\tif cpErr := s.container.CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, \"/workspace/.cloche/output/.\", outputDst); cpErr != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to extract output: %v\", runID, cpErr)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Capture full container stdout/stderr before the container is removed\n\tif logs, logErr := s.container.Logs(ctx, containerID); logErr == nil && logs != \"\" {\n\t\tcontainerLogPath := filepath.Join(outputDst, \"container.log\")\n\t\tif writeErr := os.WriteFile(containerLogPath, []byte(logs), 0644); writeErr != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to write container.log: %v\", runID, writeErr)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Index extracted log files in the log store\n\tif s.logStore != nil {\n\t\ts.indexLogFiles(ctx, runID, outputDst)\n\t}\n\n\t// Extract results to git branch BEFORE finalizing state, so that\n\t// WaitRun callers (e.g. host workflow merge step) see branches exist\n\t// before the run is marked complete.\n\tresultLabel := reportedResult\n\tif resultLabel == \"\" {\n\t\tif exitCode == 0 {\n\t\t\tresultLabel = \"succeeded\"\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tresultLabel = \"failed\"\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\t{\n\t\textractRun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n\t\tif extractRun != nil && extractRun.BaseSHA != \"\" {\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: extracting results to branch cloche/%s (baseSHA=%s)\", runID, runID, extractRun.BaseSHA)\n\t\t\tif err := docker.ExtractResults(ctx, containerID, extractRun.ProjectDir, runID, extractRun.BaseSHA, workflowName, resultLabel); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to extract results to branch: %v\", runID, err)\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: branch cloche/%s created successfully\", runID, runID)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: skipping branch extraction (baseSHA empty or run not found)\", runID)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Now finalize run state\n\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif run.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n\t\tif reportedResult == \"succeeded\" {\n\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n\t\t} else if reportedResult != \"\" {\n\t\t\tif reportedError != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\trun.Fail(reportedError)\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t} else if exitCode == 0 {\n\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"container exited with code %d\", exitCode))\n\t\t}\n\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n\t}\n\n\t// Fire evolution trigger if configured\n\tif s.evolution != nil {\n\t\ts.evolution.Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)\n\t}\n\n\t// Merge is handled as a workflow step in host.cloche, not here.\n\n\t// Container retention policy:\n\t// - Failed runs: always keep the container for debugging\n\t// - Successful runs + --keep-container: keep the container\n\t// - Successful runs without --keep-container: remove the container\n\trunFinal, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n\trunFailed := runFinal != nil && (runFinal.State == domain.RunStateFailed || runFinal.State == domain.RunStateCancelled)\n\n\tif keepContainer || runFailed {\n\t\treason := \"--keep-container\"\n\t\tif runFailed {\n\t\t\treason = \"run failed\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: keeping container %s (%s)\", runID, containerID, reason)\n\t\tif runFinal != nil {\n\t\t\trunFinal.ContainerKept = true\n\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, runFinal)\n\t\t}\n\t} else {\n\t\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to remove container %s: %v\", runID, containerID, err)\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: removed container %s\", runID, containerID)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Cleanup mapping\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tdelete(s.runIDs, runID)\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) ListRuns(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ListRunsRequest) (*pb.ListRunsResponse, error) {\n\tfilter := domain.RunListFilter{\n\t\tProjectDir: req.ProjectDir,\n\t\tState:      domain.RunState(req.State),\n\t\tTaskID:     req.TaskId,\n\t\tLimit:      int(req.Limit),\n\t}\n\n\t// When no project filter and not --all, default to last hour\n\tif filter.ProjectDir == \"\" && !req.All {\n\t\tfilter.Since = time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour)\n\t}\n\n\truns, err := s.store.ListRunsFiltered(ctx, filter)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing runs: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tresp := &pb.ListRunsResponse{}\n\tfor _, run := range runs {\n\t\tresp.Runs = append(resp.Runs, &pb.RunSummary{\n\t\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n\t\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n\t\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n\t\t\tStartedAt:    run.StartedAt.String(),\n\t\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n\t\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n\t\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n\t\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n\t\t\tProjectDir:   run.ProjectDir,\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\treturn resp, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) GetStatus(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetStatusRequest) (*pb.GetStatusResponse, error) {\n\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"getting run: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tresp := &pb.GetStatusResponse{\n\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n\t\tCurrentStep:  strings.Join(run.ActiveSteps, \",\"),\n\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n\t}\n\n\t// Check container liveness\n\tif run.ContainerID != \"\" && s.container != nil {\n\t\tif cs, err := s.container.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID); err == nil {\n\t\t\tresp.ContainerAlive = cs.Running\n\t\t\tif !cs.Running && !cs.FinishedAt.IsZero() {\n\t\t\t\tresp.ContainerDeadSince = cs.FinishedAt.Format(time.RFC3339Nano)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Load step executions from captures store if available\n\tif s.captures != nil {\n\t\tcaptures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\tfor _, exec := range captures {\n\t\t\t\tresp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n\t\t\t\t\tStepName:    exec.StepName,\n\t\t\t\t\tResult:      exec.Result,\n\t\t\t\t\tStartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t} else {\n\t\tfor _, exec := range run.StepExecutions {\n\t\t\tresp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n\t\t\t\tStepName:    exec.StepName,\n\t\t\t\tResult:      exec.Result,\n\t\t\t\tStartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn resp, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) StreamLogs(req *pb.StreamLogsRequest, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n\tctx := stream.Context()\n\n\t_ = followFromContext(ctx) // follow is implicit for active runs\n\tlimit := limitFromContext(ctx)\n\n\t// Verify run exists\n\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found: %w\", req.RunId, err)\n\t}\n\n\t// If step_name or log_type filter is set, serve content directly from the log index\n\tif req.StepName != \"\" || req.LogType != \"\" {\n\t\treturn s.streamFilteredLogs(ctx, req, run, stream, limit)\n\t}\n\n\tisActive := run.State == domain.RunStateRunning || run.State == domain.RunStatePending\n\n\t// Active runs always stream live output (follow mode is implicit).\n\t// The -f flag is accepted but redundant for active runs.\n\tif isActive && s.logBroadcast != nil {\n\t\treturn s.streamFollowLogs(req.RunId, run, stream, limit)\n\t}\n\n\t// Check for full.log first — if it exists, serve it as the unified log\n\tfullLogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n\tif data, readErr := os.ReadFile(fullLogPath); readErr == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\tmsg := applyLimit(string(data), limit)\n\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\tType:    \"full_log\",\n\t\t\tMessage: msg,\n\t\t}); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t\tif !isActive {\n\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n\t\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n\t\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn nil\n\t}\n\n\tif s.captures == nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"captures store not configured\")\n\t}\n\n\t// Fall back to capture-based streaming\n\tcaptures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"getting captures: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, exec := range captures {\n\t\t// Captures are stored as separate rows: one for step_started (no Result)\n\t\t// and one for step_completed (has Result).\n\t\tif exec.Result == \"\" {\n\t\t\tentry := &pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t\tType:      \"step_started\",\n\t\t\t\tStepName:  exec.StepName,\n\t\t\t\tTimestamp: exec.StartedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(entry); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t// Read step output from per-step output file.\n\t\t\t// Container runs write .log, host runs write .out — try both.\n\t\t\tvar output string\n\t\t\tfor _, ext := range []string{\".log\", \".out\"} {\n\t\t\t\toutputPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\", exec.StepName+ext)\n\t\t\t\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath); err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\t\t\t\toutput = string(data)\n\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tentry := &pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t\tType:      \"step_completed\",\n\t\t\t\tStepName:  exec.StepName,\n\t\t\t\tResult:    exec.Result,\n\t\t\t\tTimestamp: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t\tMessage:   applyLimit(output, limit),\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(entry); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Send run completion entry\n\tif !isActive {\n\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n\t\t}); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// followFromContext checks for the follow flag in gRPC metadata.\nfunc followFromContext(ctx context.Context) bool {\n\tmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\tvals := md.Get(\"x-cloche-follow\")\n\treturn len(vals) > 0 && vals[0] == \"true\"\n}\n\n// limitFromContext reads the line limit from gRPC metadata.\n// Returns 0 when no limit is set.\nfunc limitFromContext(ctx context.Context) int {\n\tmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn 0\n\t}\n\tvals := md.Get(\"x-cloche-limit\")\n\tif len(vals) == 0 {\n\t\treturn 0\n\t}\n\tn, err := strconv.Atoi(vals[0])\n\tif err != nil || n <= 0 {\n\t\treturn 0\n\t}\n\treturn n\n}\n\n// applyLimit returns the last n lines of content. If n <= 0, returns content unchanged.\nfunc applyLimit(content string, n int) string {\n\tif n <= 0 {\n\t\treturn content\n\t}\n\tlines := strings.Split(content, \"\\n\")\n\t// Remove trailing empty line from final newline\n\tif len(lines) > 0 && lines[len(lines)-1] == \"\" {\n\t\tlines = lines[:len(lines)-1]\n\t}\n\tif len(lines) <= n {\n\t\treturn content\n\t}\n\treturn strings.Join(lines[len(lines)-n:], \"\\n\") + \"\\n\"\n}\n\n// streamFollowLogs sends existing log content then tails live output from the\n// broadcaster. It combines snapshot + live streaming (like tail -f).\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) streamFollowLogs(runID string, run *domain.Run, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry], limit int) error {\n\t// Subscribe first so we don't miss lines written between read and subscribe.\n\tsub := s.logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)\n\tdefer s.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(runID, sub)\n\n\t// Send existing full.log content if available.\n\tfullLogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(fullLogPath); err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\tmsg := applyLimit(string(data), limit)\n\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\tType:    \"full_log\",\n\t\t\tMessage: msg,\n\t\t}); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Now tail live output from the broadcaster.\n\tctx := stream.Context()\n\tfor {\n\t\tselect {\n\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\n\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n\t\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\t\t// Run completed — send terminal entry.\n\t\t\t\tr, err := s.store.GetRun(context.Background(), runID)\n\t\t\t\tif err == nil && r.State != domain.RunStateRunning && r.State != domain.RunStatePending {\n\t\t\t\t\t_ = stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tResult:    string(r.State),\n\t\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: r.CompletedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t\t\t\tMessage:   r.ErrorMessage,\n\t\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t\tType:      \"log\",\n\t\t\t\tStepName:  line.StepName,\n\t\t\t\tMessage:   line.Content,\n\t\t\t\tTimestamp: line.Timestamp,\n\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\n// streamFilteredLogs serves log content filtered by step name and/or log type.\n// It uses the log index when available, falling back to file path conventions.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) streamFilteredLogs(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StreamLogsRequest, run *domain.Run, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry], limit int) error {\n\toutputDir := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\")\n\n\t// Try log index first\n\tif s.logStore != nil {\n\t\tvar logFiles []*ports.LogFileEntry\n\t\tvar err error\n\n\t\tif req.StepName != \"\" && req.LogType != \"\" {\n\t\t\t// Filter by both step and type\n\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, req.RunId, req.StepName)\n\t\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\t\tfiltered := logFiles[:0]\n\t\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n\t\t\t\t\tif lf.FileType == req.LogType {\n\t\t\t\t\t\tfiltered = append(filtered, lf)\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tlogFiles = filtered\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t} else if req.StepName != \"\" {\n\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, req.RunId, req.StepName)\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFileByType(ctx, req.RunId, req.LogType)\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tif err == nil && len(logFiles) > 0 {\n\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n\t\t\t\tdata, readErr := os.ReadFile(lf.FilePath)\n\t\t\t\tif readErr != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t\t\tType:     lf.FileType + \"_log\",\n\t\t\t\t\tStepName: lf.StepName,\n\t\t\t\t\tMessage:  applyLimit(string(data), limit),\n\t\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Fall back to file path conventions\n\tif req.StepName != \"\" {\n\t\tvar logPath string\n\t\tswitch req.LogType {\n\t\tcase \"llm\":\n\t\t\tlogPath = filepath.Join(outputDir, \"llm-\"+req.StepName+\".log\")\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\tlogPath = filepath.Join(outputDir, req.StepName+\".log\")\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(logPath)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"log file not found for step %q: %w\", req.StepName, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\tType:     \"step_log\",\n\t\t\tStepName: req.StepName,\n\t\t\tMessage:  applyLimit(string(data), limit),\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"no log files found matching filter\")\n}\n\n// streamLiveLogs subscribes to the broadcaster and streams log lines in real\n// time for an active run. The stream closes when the run completes or the\n// client disconnects.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) streamLiveLogs(runID string, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n\tsub := s.logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)\n\tdefer s.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(runID, sub)\n\n\tctx := stream.Context()\n\tfor {\n\t\tselect {\n\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\n\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n\t\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\t\t// Run completed — send terminal entry.\n\t\t\t\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(context.Background(), runID)\n\t\t\t\tif err == nil && run.State != domain.RunStateRunning && run.State != domain.RunStatePending {\n\t\t\t\t\t_ = stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n\t\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n\t\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t\tType:      \"log\",\n\t\t\t\tStepName:  line.StepName,\n\t\t\t\tMessage:   line.Content,\n\t\t\t\tTimestamp: line.Timestamp,\n\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) StopRun(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StopRunRequest) (*pb.StopRunResponse, error) {\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tcontainerID, ok := s.runIDs[req.RunId]\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found or already completed\", req.RunId)\n\t}\n\n\tif err := s.container.Stop(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"stopping run: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Mark as cancelled in store\n\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n\tif err == nil {\n\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateCancelled)\n\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &pb.StopRunResponse{}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) DeleteContainer(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DeleteContainerRequest) (*pb.DeleteContainerResponse, error) {\n\tif s.container == nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n\t}\n\n\tid := req.Id\n\tif id == \"\" {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"id is required\")\n\t}\n\n\t// Try to resolve as a run ID first\n\tcontainerID := id\n\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, id)\n\tif err == nil {\n\t\t// It's a run ID — use the container ID from the run record\n\t\tif run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q has no associated container\", id)\n\t\t}\n\t\tcontainerID = run.ContainerID\n\t}\n\n\t// Remove the container\n\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"removing container: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// If we resolved a run, clear the container_kept flag\n\tif run != nil {\n\t\trun.ContainerKept = false\n\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &pb.DeleteContainerResponse{}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) EnableLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.EnableLoopRequest) (*pb.EnableLoopResponse, error) {\n\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n\t}\n\n\t// Verify at least one host workflow exists in the project.\n\thostWorkflows, err := host.FindHostWorkflows(projectDir)\n\tif err != nil || len(hostWorkflows) == 0 {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no host workflows found in %s/.cloche/\", projectDir)\n\t}\n\n\t// Load project config for defaults.\n\tprojCfg, _ := config.Load(projectDir)\n\n\tmaxConc := int(req.MaxConcurrent)\n\tif maxConc <= 0 {\n\t\tmaxConc = projCfg.Orchestration.Concurrency\n\t}\n\tif maxConc <= 0 {\n\t\tmaxConc = 1\n\t}\n\n\tstagger := time.Duration(float64(time.Second) * projCfg.Orchestration.StaggerSeconds)\n\n\t// Compute dedup timeout from config (default 5 minutes).\n\tdedupTimeout := time.Duration(float64(time.Second) * projCfg.Orchestration.DedupSeconds)\n\n\tloopCfg := host.LoopConfig{\n\t\tProjectDir:    projectDir,\n\t\tMaxConcurrent: maxConc,\n\t\tStaggerDelay:  stagger,\n\t\tDedupTimeout:  dedupTimeout,\n\t\tStopOnError:   projCfg.Orchestration.StopOnError,\n\t}\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n\n\t// Stop existing loop if running.\n\tif existing, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n\t\texisting.Stop()\n\t}\n\n\t// Check if project defines a list-tasks workflow for three-phase mode.\n\tvar loop *host.Loop\n\tif _, hasListTasks := hostWorkflows[\"list-tasks\"]; hasListTasks {\n\t\tloop = s.createPhaseLoop(loopCfg, projectDir, dedupTimeout)\n\t} else {\n\t\tloop = s.createLegacyLoop(loopCfg, projectDir, projCfg, dedupTimeout)\n\t}\n\n\ts.loops[projectDir] = loop\n\tloop.Start()\n\n\treturn &pb.EnableLoopResponse{}, nil\n}\n\n// createPhaseLoop creates a three-phase orchestration loop using list-tasks,\n// main, and finalize host workflows from any .cloche file.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) createPhaseLoop(loopCfg host.LoopConfig, projectDir string, dedupTimeout time.Duration) *host.Loop {\n\t// Phase 1: list-tasks function\n\tlistTasksFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string) ([]host.Task, error) {\n\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n\t\t\tDispatcher: s,\n\t\t\tStore:      s.store,\n\t\t}\n\t\ttasks, _, err := host.RunListTasksWorkflow(ctx, runner, projDir)\n\t\treturn tasks, err\n\t}\n\n\t// Phase 2: main function\n\tmainFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"main\")\n\t}\n\n\t// Phase 3: finalize function (optional — only if a finalize host workflow exists)\n\tvar finalizeFn host.FinalizeFunc\n\tif hostWFs, err := host.FindHostWorkflows(projectDir); err == nil {\n\t\tif _, hasFinalize := hostWFs[\"finalize\"]; hasFinalize {\n\t\t\tfinalizeFn = func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string, mainResult *host.RunResult) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n\t\t\t\tmainRunID := \"\"\n\t\t\t\tmainOutcome := \"failed\"\n\t\t\t\tif mainResult != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tmainRunID = mainResult.RunID\n\t\t\t\t\tmainOutcome = string(mainResult.State)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n\t\t\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n\t\t\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n\t\t\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n\t\t\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n\t\t\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n\t\t\t\t\tExtraEnv: []string{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID=\" + mainRunID,\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME=\" + mainOutcome,\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\treturn runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"finalize\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tlog.Printf(\"orchestration loop: three-phase mode enabled for %s (list-tasks + main + finalize, dedup=%s)\", projectDir, dedupTimeout)\n\treturn host.NewPhaseLoop(loopCfg, s.store, listTasksFn, mainFn, finalizeFn)\n}\n\n// createLegacyLoop creates a legacy single-function orchestration loop.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) createLegacyLoop(loopCfg host.LoopConfig, projectDir string, projCfg *config.Config, dedupTimeout time.Duration) *host.Loop {\n\trunFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn runner.Run(ctx, projDir)\n\t}\n\n\tloop := host.NewLoop(loopCfg, s.store, runFn)\n\n\t// Configure daemon-managed task assignment if a list-tasks command is set.\n\tif cmd := projCfg.Orchestration.ListTasksCommand; cmd != \"\" {\n\t\tloop.SetTaskAssigner(&host.ScriptTaskAssigner{Command: cmd})\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"orchestration loop: task assignment enabled for %s (command=%q, dedup=%s)\", projectDir, cmd, dedupTimeout)\n\t}\n\n\treturn loop\n}\n\n// GetLoopTasks returns the current task pipeline state for a project's\n// orchestration loop, formatted as web.TaskEntry values. Returns nil if no\n// loop is active for the project.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) GetLoopTasks(projectDir string) []web.TaskEntry {\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tloop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn nil\n\t}\n\tsnapshot := loop.GetTaskSnapshot()\n\n\t// Build a set of task IDs that have active (pending/running) runs.\n\tactiveTaskIDs := make(map[string]bool)\n\tctx := context.Background()\n\tallRuns, _ := s.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, time.Time{})\n\tfor _, r := range allRuns {\n\t\tif r.TaskID != \"\" && (r.State == domain.RunStatePending || r.State == domain.RunStateRunning) {\n\t\t\tactiveTaskIDs[r.TaskID] = true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tentries := make([]web.TaskEntry, len(snapshot))\n\tfor i, e := range snapshot {\n\t\tentry := web.TaskEntry{\n\t\t\tID:          e.Task.ID,\n\t\t\tStatus:      e.Task.Status,\n\t\t\tTitle:       e.Task.Title,\n\t\t\tDescription: e.Task.Description,\n\t\t\tMetadata:    e.Task.Metadata,\n\t\t\tAssigned:    e.Assigned,\n\t\t\tRunID:       e.RunID,\n\t\t}\n\t\tif !e.AssignedAt.IsZero() {\n\t\t\tentry.AssignedAt = e.AssignedAt.Format(time.RFC3339)\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Stale: task is in_progress but has no active worker.\n\t\tif host.TaskStatus(e.Task.Status) == host.TaskStatusInProgress && !activeTaskIDs[e.Task.ID] {\n\t\t\tentry.Stale = true\n\t\t}\n\t\tentries[i] = entry\n\t}\n\treturn entries\n}\n\n// ReleaseTask runs the release-task host workflow for a specific task,\n// returning it to open status.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) ReleaseTask(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, taskID string) error {\n\trunner := &host.Runner{\n\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n\t\tStore:        s.store,\n\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n\t}\n\tresult, err := runner.RunNamed(ctx, projectDir, \"release-task\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"release-task workflow failed: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tif result.State != domain.RunStateSucceeded {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"release-task workflow finished with state %s\", result.State)\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) DisableLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DisableLoopRequest) (*pb.DisableLoopResponse, error) {\n\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n\t}\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n\n\tif loop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n\t\tloop.Stop()\n\t\tdelete(s.loops, projectDir)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &pb.DisableLoopResponse{}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) ResumeLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ResumeLoopRequest) (*pb.ResumeLoopResponse, error) {\n\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n\t}\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tloop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\n\tif !ok || loop == nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no orchestration loop for %s\", projectDir)\n\t}\n\n\tloop.Resume()\n\treturn &pb.ResumeLoopResponse{}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) GetProjectInfo(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetProjectInfoRequest) (*pb.GetProjectInfoResponse, error) {\n\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n\n\t// Resolve by name if provided.\n\tif req.Name != \"\" && projectDir == \"\" {\n\t\tprojects, err := s.store.ListProjects(ctx)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing projects: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\t\tfound := false\n\t\tfor dir, label := range labels {\n\t\t\tif label == req.Name {\n\t\t\t\tprojectDir = dir\n\t\t\t\tfound = true\n\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\tif !found {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project %q not found\", req.Name)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir or name is required\")\n\t}\n\n\t// Derive project label.\n\tprojects, _ := s.store.ListProjects(ctx)\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\tlabel := labels[projectDir]\n\tif label == \"\" {\n\t\tlabel = filepath.Base(projectDir)\n\t}\n\n\t// Load config.\n\tcfg, _ := config.Load(projectDir)\n\n\t// Check loop state.\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tloop, loopExists := s.loops[projectDir]\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\tloopRunning := loopExists && loop != nil && loop.Running()\n\n\t// Get active runs.\n\tallRuns, _ := s.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, time.Time{})\n\tvar activeRuns []*pb.RunSummary\n\tfor _, run := range allRuns {\n\t\tif run.State == domain.RunStatePending || run.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n\t\t\tactiveRuns = append(activeRuns, &pb.RunSummary{\n\t\t\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n\t\t\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n\t\t\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n\t\t\t\tStartedAt:    run.StartedAt.String(),\n\t\t\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n\t\t\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n\t\t\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Discover workflows.\n\tvar containerWorkflows, hostWorkflows []string\n\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\")\n\tentries, _ := filepath.Glob(filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"*.cloche\"))\n\tfor _, path := range entries {\n\t\tbase := filepath.Base(path)\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tif base == \"host.cloche\" {\n\t\t\twfs, err := dsl.ParseAllForHost(string(data))\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tfor name := range wfs {\n\t\t\t\thostWorkflows = append(hostWorkflows, name)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\twf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tcontainerWorkflows = append(containerWorkflows, wf.Name)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tsort.Strings(containerWorkflows)\n\tsort.Strings(hostWorkflows)\n\n\t// Check if loop is halted due to an error.\n\tvar errorHalted bool\n\tvar haltError string\n\tif loopExists && loop != nil {\n\t\terrorHalted, haltError = loop.Halted()\n\t}\n\n\treturn &pb.GetProjectInfoResponse{\n\t\tProjectDir:         projectDir,\n\t\tName:               label,\n\t\tActive:             cfg.Active,\n\t\tConcurrency:        int32(cfg.Orchestration.Concurrency),\n\t\tStaggerSeconds:     cfg.Orchestration.StaggerSeconds,\n\t\tDedupSeconds:       cfg.Orchestration.DedupSeconds,\n\t\tEvolutionEnabled:   cfg.Evolution.Enabled,\n\t\tLoopRunning:        loopRunning,\n\t\tActiveRuns:         activeRuns,\n\t\tContainerWorkflows: containerWorkflows,\n\t\tHostWorkflows:      hostWorkflows,\n\t\tStopOnError:        cfg.Orchestration.StopOnError,\n\t\tErrorHalted:        errorHalted,\n\t\tHaltError:          haltError,\n\t}, nil\n}\n\n// projectLabels maps each project directory to a short display label.\n// Uses basename unless there are conflicts, in which case parent/basename is used.\nfunc projectLabels(dirs []string) map[string]string {\n\tlabels := make(map[string]string, len(dirs))\n\tbyBase := map[string][]string{}\n\tfor _, d := range dirs {\n\t\tbase := filepath.Base(d)\n\t\tbyBase[base] = append(byBase[base], d)\n\t}\n\tfor base, paths := range byBase {\n\t\tif len(paths) == 1 {\n\t\t\tlabels[paths[0]] = base\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tfor _, p := range paths {\n\t\t\t\tparent := filepath.Base(filepath.Dir(p))\n\t\t\t\tlabels[p] = parent + \"/\" + base\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn labels\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetVersionRequest) (*pb.GetVersionResponse, error) {\n\treturn &pb.GetVersionResponse{Version: version.Version()}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) Shutdown(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ShutdownRequest) (*pb.ShutdownResponse, error) {\n\tif !req.Force {\n\t\t// Check for active container runs.\n\t\ts.mu.Lock()\n\t\tactiveRuns := len(s.runIDs)\n\t\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\t\tif activeRuns > 0 {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"cannot shutdown: %d run(s) still active (use --force to override)\", activeRuns)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Stop all orchestration loops.\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tfor _, loop := range s.loops {\n\t\tloop.Stop()\n\t}\n\ts.loops = make(map[string]*host.Loop)\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\n\tif s.shutdownFn == nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"shutdown not configured\")\n\t}\n\tgo s.shutdownFn()\n\treturn &pb.ShutdownResponse{}, nil\n}\n\n// indexLogFiles scans the extracted output directory and creates log_files index entries.\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) indexLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID, outputDir string) {\n\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(outputDir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to read output dir for indexing: %v\", runID, err)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tnow := time.Now()\n\tfor _, entry := range entries {\n\t\tif entry.IsDir() {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tname := entry.Name()\n\t\tif !strings.HasSuffix(name, \".log\") {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tvar fileType, stepName string\n\t\tbase := strings.TrimSuffix(name, \".log\")\n\n\t\tswitch {\n\t\tcase name == \"full.log\":\n\t\t\tfileType = \"full\"\n\t\tcase name == \"container.log\":\n\t\t\t// container.log is internal, not indexed as a user-facing log type\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\tcase strings.HasPrefix(name, \"llm-\"):\n\t\t\tfileType = \"llm\"\n\t\t\tstepName = strings.TrimPrefix(base, \"llm-\")\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\tfileType = \"script\"\n\t\t\tstepName = base\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tinfo, _ := entry.Info()\n\t\tvar fileSize int64\n\t\tif info != nil {\n\t\t\tfileSize = info.Size()\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tlogEntry := &ports.LogFileEntry{\n\t\t\tRunID:     runID,\n\t\t\tStepName:  stepName,\n\t\t\tFileType:  fileType,\n\t\t\tFilePath:  filepath.Join(outputDir, name),\n\t\t\tFileSize:  fileSize,\n\t\t\tCreatedAt: now,\n\t\t}\n\t\tif err := s.logStore.SaveLogFile(ctx, logEntry); err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to index log file %s: %v\", runID, name, err)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc gitHEAD(dir string) string {\n\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\")\n\tcmd.Dir = dir\n\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\treturn strings.TrimSpace(string(out))\n}\n","numLines":1354,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1354}}}
